1
00:00:23,358 --> 00:00:26,194
[Theme song plays]

2
00:03:13,695 --> 00:03:16,114
[Chains rattling]

3
00:03:31,212 --> 00:03:32,964
[Man grunting]

4
00:03:38,261 --> 00:03:40,138
[Horse nickering]

5
00:03:54,319 --> 00:03:56,863
- Whoa.
- [Horses snorting]

6
00:03:57,030 --> 00:03:59,699
[Gentle metallic rattling]

7
00:04:03,161 --> 00:04:04,329
Whoa.

8
00:04:18,760 --> 00:04:21,971
Who's that stumblin'
around in the dark?

9
00:04:22,138 --> 00:04:25,934
State your business
or prepare to get winged!

10
00:04:26,100 --> 00:04:28,686
Calm yourselves, gentlemen.

11
00:04:28,853 --> 00:04:31,189
I mean you no harm.

12
00:04:31,356 --> 00:04:36,194
I'm simply a fellow weary traveler.
Whoa, boy.

13
00:04:37,528 --> 00:04:39,197
Good cold evening, gentlemen.

14
00:04:39,364 --> 00:04:41,699
I'm looKing for a pair of slave traders

15
00:04:41,866 --> 00:04:43,534
that go by the name
of the Speck brothers.

16
00:04:43,701 --> 00:04:45,536
Might that be you?

17
00:04:46,913 --> 00:04:49,666
- Who wants to know?
- Well, I do.

18
00:04:49,832 --> 00:04:51,709
I'm Dr. King Schultz.
This is my horse, Fritz.

19
00:04:51,876 --> 00:04:52,794
[Snorting]

20
00:04:52,961 --> 00:04:56,464
- What kinda doctor?
- [Schultz] Dentist.

21
00:04:56,631 --> 00:04:58,424
Now, are you the Speck brothers?

22
00:04:58,591 --> 00:05:01,386
And did you purchase those men
at the Greenville slave auction?

23
00:05:01,552 --> 00:05:04,138
- So what?
- So I wish to parley with you.

24
00:05:04,305 --> 00:05:07,642
- Speak English.
- [Chuckles] Oh, I'm sorry.

25
00:05:07,809 --> 00:05:10,019
Please forgive me.
It is a second language.

26
00:05:10,186 --> 00:05:13,481
Now, amongst your inventory,
I've been led to believe,

27
00:05:13,648 --> 00:05:16,067
is a specimen I'm keen to acquire.

28
00:05:16,234 --> 00:05:17,694
Hello, you poor devils!

29
00:05:19,028 --> 00:05:21,614
Is there one amongst you
who was formerly a resident

30
00:05:21,781 --> 00:05:25,076
of the Carrucan plantation?

31
00:05:25,827 --> 00:05:28,037
[Man] I'm from the Carrucan plantation.

32
00:05:29,664 --> 00:05:31,040
Who said that?

33
00:05:38,589 --> 00:05:39,841
[Schultz lighting match]

34
00:06:18,254 --> 00:06:19,630
What's your name?

35
00:06:23,801 --> 00:06:25,678
Django.

36
00:06:25,845 --> 00:06:28,598
Then you are exactly
the one I'm looKing for.

37
00:06:30,475 --> 00:06:32,685
Do you know who
the Brittle brothers are?

38
00:06:36,314 --> 00:06:37,315
Who are they?

39
00:06:39,734 --> 00:06:41,360
Big John.

40
00:06:42,153 --> 00:06:43,488
Ellis.

41
00:06:44,906 --> 00:06:48,826
Roger.
Sometime they call him Lil Raj.

42
00:06:50,203 --> 00:06:52,413
They was overseers
at the Carrucan plantation.

43
00:06:52,580 --> 00:06:53,664
Not anymore.

44
00:06:56,751 --> 00:06:57,794
Tell me...

45
00:06:58,377 --> 00:07:01,172
...if you were to see
any of these three gentlemen again,

46
00:07:01,339 --> 00:07:04,008
- would you recognize them?
- [Man] Hey.

47
00:07:04,175 --> 00:07:06,636
- Stop talkin' to him like that.
- Like what?

48
00:07:06,803 --> 00:07:08,346
Like that.

49
00:07:08,513 --> 00:07:10,807
My good man,
I'm simply trying to ascertain...

50
00:07:10,973 --> 00:07:13,017
Speak English, goddamn it.

51
00:07:13,184 --> 00:07:14,936
Everybody calm down.

52
00:07:15,103 --> 00:07:18,815
I'm simply a customer
trying to conduct a transaction.

53
00:07:18,981 --> 00:07:21,984
I don't care. No sale.
Now, off with ya.

54
00:07:22,151 --> 00:07:25,154
[Scoffs] Don't be ridiculous.
Of course they're for sale.

55
00:07:25,988 --> 00:07:27,448
Move it.

56
00:07:27,615 --> 00:07:32,537
My good man, did you simply get carried
away with your dramatic gesture

57
00:07:32,703 --> 00:07:36,499
or are you pointing your weapon at me
with lethal intention?

58
00:07:37,583 --> 00:07:39,460
Last chance, fancy pants.

59
00:07:40,878 --> 00:07:43,214
Oh, very well.

60
00:07:43,881 --> 00:07:44,924
[Horse whinnying]

61
00:07:46,509 --> 00:07:48,845
[Man screaming]

62
00:07:52,974 --> 00:07:54,642
[Scream echoing]

63
00:08:07,530 --> 00:08:10,241
[Screaming continues]

64
00:08:11,993 --> 00:08:14,412
I'm sorry to put a bullet in your beast,

65
00:08:14,579 --> 00:08:16,497
but I didn't want you
to do anything rash

66
00:08:16,664 --> 00:08:18,958
before you had a moment
to come to your senses.

67
00:08:19,125 --> 00:08:22,545
You goddamn son of a bitch!

68
00:08:22,712 --> 00:08:25,506
- You shot Roscoe!
- Well...

69
00:08:25,673 --> 00:08:27,383
And you killed ace!

70
00:08:27,550 --> 00:08:30,219
I only shot your brother once
he threatened to shoot me.

71
00:08:30,386 --> 00:08:33,222
And I do believe I have...
One, two, three, four...

72
00:08:33,389 --> 00:08:36,350
...five witnesses
who can attest to that fact.

73
00:08:36,517 --> 00:08:39,395
- Damn leg's busted!
- No doubt.

74
00:08:39,562 --> 00:08:42,106
Now, if you could keep your
caterwauling down to a minimum,

75
00:08:42,273 --> 00:08:45,610
I'd like to finish my line
of inquiry with young Django.

76
00:08:45,776 --> 00:08:47,778
[Screaming resumes]

77
00:08:49,614 --> 00:08:53,075
- [Man] God-fuckin'-damn it!
- As I was saying...

78
00:08:53,242 --> 00:08:56,954
...if you were to see the Brittle
brothers again, you could recognize 'em?

79
00:08:57,622 --> 00:08:59,332
Yeah.

80
00:08:59,498 --> 00:09:00,791
Sold American!

81
00:09:00,958 --> 00:09:04,921
So, Mr. Speck? Mr. Speck?
How much for young Django here?

82
00:09:10,218 --> 00:09:12,845
That iron is nasty business.

83
00:09:18,059 --> 00:09:20,186
Oh, could you hold this for a moment?

84
00:09:21,687 --> 00:09:21,854
Thank you. Django?

85
00:09:23,731 --> 00:09:23,898
Get up on that horse.

86
00:09:25,691 --> 00:09:25,858
Also, if I were you,

87
00:09:29,862 --> 00:09:37,862
I'd take that winter coat
the dear departed Speck left behind.

88
00:09:47,880 --> 00:09:55,880
Nigger!
Don't you touch my brother's coat.

89
00:09:58,391 --> 00:09:58,558
[Screaming]

90
00:10:03,479 --> 00:10:05,148
Goddamn it! Oh!
[Moaning]

91
00:10:10,319 --> 00:10:10,486
One hundred... ten... 20...

92
00:10:12,321 --> 00:10:13,573
...and five...

93
00:10:14,740 --> 00:10:14,907
...for young Django here.

94
00:10:17,076 --> 00:10:17,243
And since he won't
be needing it anymore,

95
00:10:19,745 --> 00:10:20,454
I'd like to purchase your brother's nag.

96
00:10:25,418 --> 00:10:25,585
Also, Mr. Speck, I'm afraid
I will require a bill of sale.

97
00:10:27,170 --> 00:10:27,336
Do you have one?

98
00:10:30,256 --> 00:10:30,423
- You go to hell, dentist.
- [Scoffs]

99
00:10:32,425 --> 00:10:32,592
I thought not.

100
00:10:36,095 --> 00:10:40,433
No worries. I come prepared.

101
00:10:42,018 --> 00:10:42,185
Thank you.

102
00:10:45,771 --> 00:10:50,693
This will serve nicely
as a bill of sale.

103
00:10:52,278 --> 00:10:58,117
[Nickering]

104
00:10:59,118 --> 00:11:03,289
Whoa.

105
00:11:06,751 --> 00:11:06,918
Now, as to you poor devils.

106
00:11:11,964 --> 00:11:12,131
So, as I see it, when it comes to
the subject of what to do next,

107
00:11:14,967 --> 00:11:15,134
you gentlemen have two choices.

108
00:11:20,264 --> 00:11:20,431
One: Once I'm gone, you could lift
that beast off the remaining Speck,

109
00:11:22,350 --> 00:11:22,516
then carry him to the nearest town.

110
00:11:26,103 --> 00:11:26,270
Which would be at least
37 Miles back the way you came.

111
00:11:31,943 --> 00:11:32,109
Or two: You could unshackle yourselves,
take that rifle,

112
00:11:34,654 --> 00:11:34,820
put a bullet in his head,
bury the two of them deep,

113
00:11:38,366 --> 00:11:39,450
and then make your way to a
more enlightened area of this country.

114
00:11:40,618 --> 00:11:40,785
Choice is yours.

115
00:11:45,164 --> 00:11:45,331
Oh, and on the off chance there are
any astronomy aficionados amongst you,

116
00:11:48,334 --> 00:11:49,794
the north star is that one.

117
00:11:52,964 --> 00:12:00,964
Ta-ta. [ClucKing]

118
00:12:11,857 --> 00:12:12,108
Now wait a minute, fellas.
Let's talk about this!

119
00:12:15,319 --> 00:12:15,486
- [Lantern crashing]
- [Chains rattling]

120
00:12:18,906 --> 00:12:20,366
You gotta be reasonable
in a situation like this!

121
00:12:23,369 --> 00:12:23,536
I'm not a bad guy.
I'm just doin' my job!

122
00:12:27,123 --> 00:12:27,290
Blueberry, didn't I
give you my last apple?

123
00:12:30,251 --> 00:12:30,418
Tell you what, boys:
Take me to the Doc in El Paso,

124
00:12:32,461 --> 00:12:32,628
- I'll get you your freedom.
- [Gun cocKing]

125
00:12:36,382 --> 00:12:44,382
- No. No, please...
- [Gunshot echoing]

126
00:12:53,941 --> 00:13:01,941
[Dogs barKing nearby]

127
00:13:21,052 --> 00:13:21,719
[SqueaKing]

128
00:13:23,095 --> 00:13:23,262
All right, now.

129
00:13:25,264 --> 00:13:25,431
I'd like you to
take two of these tonight...

130
00:13:27,641 --> 00:13:29,769
- [Coughing]
- ...And then in the morning...

131
00:13:31,562 --> 00:13:39,562
That's a nigger on a horse.

132
00:13:58,964 --> 00:13:59,131
What's everybody staring at?

133
00:14:01,634 --> 00:14:02,843
They ain't never seen
no nigger on a horse before.

134
00:14:05,096 --> 00:14:13,096
[Goats bleating]

135
00:14:14,939 --> 00:14:22,939
Whoa.

136
00:14:26,992 --> 00:14:28,327
Good morning, innkeeper!

137
00:14:30,788 --> 00:14:30,955
Two beers for two weary travelers.

138
00:14:32,706 --> 00:14:32,873
It's still a bit early.

139
00:14:35,292 --> 00:14:35,459
We won't be open for another hour.

140
00:14:37,294 --> 00:14:37,461
By then, we'll be servin' breakfast.

141
00:14:42,883 --> 00:14:43,050
[Gasping] Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa... what
the hell you think you're doing, boy?

142
00:14:45,136 --> 00:14:48,681
Get that nigger outta here!

143
00:14:52,685 --> 00:14:52,852
- [Panting] Help! Help!
- Innkeeper!

144
00:14:56,021 --> 00:14:56,188
Remember, get the sheriff,
not the marshal.

145
00:14:58,065 --> 00:14:58,232
[Man] Sheriff! Help!

146
00:14:59,859 --> 00:15:01,235
Alas.

147
00:15:03,779 --> 00:15:06,198
Now we must act as our own bartender.

148
00:15:07,950 --> 00:15:15,950
Sit down, my boy.

149
00:15:20,504 --> 00:15:21,338
- What kind of dentist are you?
- [Chortles]

150
00:15:25,926 --> 00:15:30,556
Despite that cart, I haven't
practiced dentistry in five years.

151
00:15:33,851 --> 00:15:36,061
But these days,
I practice a new profession...

152
00:15:37,438 --> 00:15:44,028
...Bounty Hunter.

153
00:15:45,863 --> 00:15:46,572
Do you know what a bounty hunter is?

154
00:15:47,615 --> 00:15:47,781
No.

155
00:15:48,991 --> 00:15:50,618
Well...

156
00:15:54,747 --> 00:15:54,914
...the way the slave trade
deals in human lives for cash,

157
00:15:57,249 --> 00:15:57,416
a bounty hunter deals in corpses.

158
00:15:59,627 --> 00:16:03,380
[TsKing] Hat

159
00:16:04,924 --> 00:16:12,924
prost.

160
00:16:15,768 --> 00:16:15,935
The state places a bounty
on a man's head.

161
00:16:18,604 --> 00:16:18,771
I track that man, I find that man,
I kill that man.

162
00:16:22,733 --> 00:16:22,900
After I've killed him, I transport that
man's corpse back to the authorities.

163
00:16:25,611 --> 00:16:25,778
Sometimes that's easier said than done.

164
00:16:28,572 --> 00:16:28,739
I show that corpse to the authorities,
proving yes, indeed,

165
00:16:30,449 --> 00:16:30,616
I truly have killed him,

166
00:16:33,619 --> 00:16:33,786
at which point the authorities
pay me the bounty.

167
00:16:37,122 --> 00:16:38,749
So, like slavery,
it's a flesh for cash business.

168
00:16:39,750 --> 00:16:43,546
What's a bounty?

169
00:16:45,005 --> 00:16:45,172
It's like a reward.

170
00:16:48,551 --> 00:16:48,717
You kill people?
And they give you a reward?

171
00:16:50,594 --> 00:16:50,761
Certain people, yeah.

172
00:16:51,887 --> 00:16:52,054
Bad people?

173
00:16:56,016 --> 00:16:56,183
Ah! Badder they are,
bigger the reward.

174
00:16:58,477 --> 00:16:58,644
Which brings me to you.

175
00:17:02,898 --> 00:17:03,065
And I must admit, I'm at a bit of
a quandary when it comes to you.

176
00:17:05,484 --> 00:17:05,651
On one hand, I despise slavery.

177
00:17:08,779 --> 00:17:08,946
On the other hand, I need your help.

178
00:17:12,324 --> 00:17:13,200
If you're not in a position to refuse,
all the better.

179
00:17:15,869 --> 00:17:16,036
So, for the time being, I'm gonna
make this slavery malarkey

180
00:17:18,247 --> 00:17:18,414
work to my benefit.

181
00:17:23,085 --> 00:17:24,753
Still, having said that, I feel guilty.

182
00:17:30,009 --> 00:17:37,057
So, I would like the two of us
to enter into an agreement.

183
00:17:38,892 --> 00:17:43,564
I'm looKing for the Brittle brothers.

184
00:17:44,898 --> 00:17:45,065
However, at this endeavor,

185
00:17:50,195 --> 00:17:51,447
I'm at a slight disadvantage insofar
as I don't know what they look like.

186
00:17:54,325 --> 00:17:54,491
But you do. Don't ya?

187
00:17:56,702 --> 00:17:56,869
I know what they look like all right.

188
00:18:00,372 --> 00:18:00,539
Good. So here's my agreement.

189
00:18:03,959 --> 00:18:04,126
- You travel with me until we find them.
- Where we goin'?

190
00:18:06,754 --> 00:18:06,920
I hear at least two of them
are overseeing up in Gatlinburg,

191
00:18:09,089 --> 00:18:09,256
but I don't know where.

192
00:18:13,552 --> 00:18:13,719
That means we visit every plantation
in Gatlinburg till we find 'em.

193
00:18:18,974 --> 00:18:20,017
And when we find them,
you point them out, and I kill them.

194
00:18:23,395 --> 00:18:23,562
You do that, I agree
to give you your freedom,

195
00:18:27,691 --> 00:18:27,858
$25 per Brittle brother. That's $75.

196
00:18:31,570 --> 00:18:35,407
And, as if on cue,
here comes the sheriff.

197
00:18:36,659 --> 00:18:39,328
[Scoffs]

198
00:18:44,833 --> 00:18:47,461
Ok, boys. Fun's over. Come on out.

199
00:18:52,049 --> 00:18:53,092
- [Overlapping chatter]
- All right, folks, calm down.

200
00:18:54,802 --> 00:18:55,594
Go about your business.

201
00:18:57,971 --> 00:18:59,932
These jokers will be gone soon.

202
00:19:05,354 --> 00:19:05,521
Now, why y'all wanna come
into my town and start trouble?

203
00:19:08,774 --> 00:19:09,942
And scare all these nice people.

204
00:19:12,611 --> 00:19:12,778
You ain't got nothing better to do

205
00:19:15,989 --> 00:19:16,156
than to come into bill sharp's town

206
00:19:18,409 --> 00:19:18,575
and show your ass?

207
00:19:20,327 --> 00:19:20,494
- [Metal springing noise]
- [Sheriff screaming]

208
00:19:23,455 --> 00:19:23,622
- [Crowd gasping]
- [Groaning]

209
00:19:24,998 --> 00:19:26,750
[Woman screams]

210
00:19:30,671 --> 00:19:32,131
- What'd you just do to our sheriff?
- [Groaning]

211
00:19:34,007 --> 00:19:34,174
- [Yelling]
- [Shot echoing]

212
00:19:35,384 --> 00:19:35,551
[Woman gasps]

213
00:19:37,511 --> 00:19:41,974
[Crowd screaming]

214
00:19:44,309 --> 00:19:45,811
Now you can get the marshal.

215
00:19:48,147 --> 00:19:48,313
[Man] Marshal! Marshal!

216
00:19:50,566 --> 00:19:50,733
- Should we wait inside?
- Can we just leave?

217
00:19:51,942 --> 00:19:54,403
After you.

218
00:19:58,615 --> 00:19:58,782
Move that buckboard a long ways
across the street from the saloon.

219
00:20:01,660 --> 00:20:01,827
I want six men, six rifles behind it.

220
00:20:03,996 --> 00:20:04,163
I want two men,
two rifles up on this roof.

221
00:20:06,498 --> 00:20:06,665
Two men, two rifles on that roof.

222
00:20:09,626 --> 00:20:09,793
All the barrels aimed
at that front door.

223
00:20:12,796 --> 00:20:13,964
Somebody get poor bill
outta the goddamn street.

224
00:20:16,133 --> 00:20:16,300
You in the saloon!

225
00:20:19,636 --> 00:20:20,345
We got a hundred rifles aimed
at every way out of that buildin'.

226
00:20:23,515 --> 00:20:24,349
You got one chance
to get out of this alive.

227
00:20:26,852 --> 00:20:27,019
You and your nigger come out right now
with your hands over your head,

228
00:20:28,979 --> 00:20:30,105
and I mean right now.

229
00:20:33,525 --> 00:20:33,692
[Schultz] Is this the marshal
I have the pleasure of addressing?

230
00:20:35,486 --> 00:20:35,652
Yes, it is.

231
00:20:37,738 --> 00:20:37,905
This is U.S. Marshal Gill Tatum.

232
00:20:40,199 --> 00:20:40,699
[Schultz]
Na wunderbar, marshal.

233
00:20:44,286 --> 00:20:44,453
I have relieved myself of all weapons,

234
00:20:47,372 --> 00:20:47,539
and just as you have instructed,

235
00:20:50,209 --> 00:20:50,375
I am ready to step outside

236
00:20:54,463 --> 00:20:55,547
with my hands raised above my head.

237
00:20:57,966 --> 00:20:58,133
I trust as a representative

238
00:21:01,512 --> 00:21:01,678
of the criminal justice system of
the United States of America,

239
00:21:07,518 --> 00:21:07,684
I shan't be shot down in the street
by either you or your deputies

240
00:21:10,521 --> 00:21:10,687
before I've had my day in court.

241
00:21:13,023 --> 00:21:13,190
You mean like you did our sheriff.

242
00:21:14,983 --> 00:21:15,150
Shot him down like a dog in the street.

243
00:21:17,486 --> 00:21:17,653
Yes, that's exactly what I mean.

244
00:21:23,325 --> 00:21:26,662
Do I have your word as a lawman not to
shoot me down like a dog in the street?

245
00:21:29,915 --> 00:21:30,082
Well, much as we'd all enjoy
seeing something like that,

246
00:21:33,085 --> 00:21:34,127
ain't nobody gonna cheat
the hangman in my town.

247
00:21:37,089 --> 00:21:38,924
Fair enough, marshal.
Here we come.

248
00:21:41,093 --> 00:21:41,260
They're a little tense out there.

249
00:21:44,721 --> 00:21:45,055
So don't make any quick movements,
and let me do the talKing.

250
00:21:47,724 --> 00:21:54,773
- [Doors squeaKing open]
- Come ahead.

251
00:21:56,024 --> 00:21:56,191
You unarmed?

252
00:21:57,901 --> 00:21:58,652
[Schultz] Yes, indeed we are.

253
00:22:01,989 --> 00:22:02,155
Marshal Tatum, may I address you
and your deputies,

254
00:22:04,116 --> 00:22:04,283
and apparently the
entire town of Daughtrey,

255
00:22:06,618 --> 00:22:07,953
as to the incident that just occurred?

256
00:22:10,414 --> 00:22:10,581
- Go on.
- Thank you.

257
00:22:12,708 --> 00:22:12,875
My name is Dr. King Schultz.

258
00:22:16,128 --> 00:22:16,295
Like yourself, marshal,
I'm a servant of the court.

259
00:22:19,715 --> 00:22:19,882
The man lying dead in the dirt,
who the good people of Daughtrey

260
00:22:23,969 --> 00:22:24,136
saw fit to elect as their sheriff,
who went by the name of Bill Sharp,

261
00:22:28,724 --> 00:22:28,891
is actually a wanted outlaw
by the name of Willard Peck,

262
00:22:31,476 --> 00:22:31,643
with a price on his head of $200.

263
00:22:34,605 --> 00:22:34,771
Now that's $200, dead or alive.

264
00:22:36,106 --> 00:22:36,273
The hell, you say!

265
00:22:40,319 --> 00:22:40,485
I'm aware this is probably
disconcerting news.

266
00:22:43,655 --> 00:22:43,822
But I'm willing to wager
this man was elected sheriff

267
00:22:46,325 --> 00:22:47,242
sometime in the past two years?

268
00:22:48,243 --> 00:22:48,410
Yeah.

269
00:22:51,830 --> 00:22:51,997
[Schultz] I know this because three
years ago, he was rustling cattle

270
00:22:55,459 --> 00:22:55,626
from the B.C. Corrigan Cattle Company
of Lubbock, Texas.

271
00:22:59,421 --> 00:22:59,588
Now, this is a warrant
made out by

272
00:23:05,260 --> 00:23:05,427
circuit court judge Henry Allen
Laudermilk of Austin, Texas.

273
00:23:07,137 --> 00:23:07,304
You're encouraged to wire him.

274
00:23:12,351 --> 00:23:12,517
He'll back up who I am and
who your dear departed sheriff was.

275
00:23:16,480 --> 00:23:20,525
[Guns uncocKing]

276
00:23:24,446 --> 00:23:24,613
In other words, marshal,
you owe me $200.

277
00:23:27,532 --> 00:23:33,121
[Medium-tempo song plays]

278
00:23:34,623 --> 00:23:42,623
I'll be damned.

279
00:24:06,238 --> 00:24:06,405
After this Brittle business
is behind us,

280
00:24:11,952 --> 00:24:14,746
you'll be a free man, with a horse,
$75 in your back pocket...

281
00:24:16,164 --> 00:24:18,417
What's your plan after that?

282
00:24:22,254 --> 00:24:24,506
Find my wife, and buy her freedom.

283
00:24:29,386 --> 00:24:29,886
Django, I had no idea
you were a married man.

284
00:24:32,180 --> 00:24:32,347
Do most slaves believe in marriage?

285
00:24:35,934 --> 00:24:36,101
Oh, me and my wife do.

286
00:24:40,272 --> 00:24:41,481
Old man Carrucan didn't.
That's why we, uh... we run off.

287
00:24:43,108 --> 00:24:43,775
[Man] Django.

288
00:24:46,361 --> 00:24:46,528
Django, Django-

289
00:24:49,239 --> 00:24:49,948
you got sand, Django.

290
00:24:51,825 --> 00:24:53,618
Boy's got sand.

291
00:24:56,747 --> 00:24:58,457
I got no use for a nigger with sand.

292
00:25:01,960 --> 00:25:02,127
I want you to burn a runaway "r"
right here on his cheek.

293
00:25:03,170 --> 00:25:03,336
And the girl, too.

294
00:25:05,130 --> 00:25:05,297
[Groaning]

295
00:25:10,093 --> 00:25:10,927
And I want you to take 'em to
the Greenville auction and sell 'em.

296
00:25:12,804 --> 00:25:12,971
Both of 'em.

297
00:25:14,723 --> 00:25:17,184
Separately.

298
00:25:18,518 --> 00:25:21,146
And this one...

299
00:25:23,857 --> 00:25:25,817
...you will sell him cheap.

300
00:25:27,319 --> 00:25:29,863
In Greenville...

301
00:25:32,824 --> 00:25:40,040
...there should be some sort
of a records office.

302
00:25:42,250 --> 00:25:43,710
You know when she was sold...

303
00:25:46,671 --> 00:25:46,838
...you know where she came from,

304
00:25:48,673 --> 00:25:49,466
and you know her name.

305
00:25:51,009 --> 00:25:51,176
What is her name?

306
00:25:52,844 --> 00:25:54,429
Broomhilda.

307
00:25:57,682 --> 00:25:57,849
- What?
- Broom-hilda.

308
00:25:59,810 --> 00:26:01,895
- Broomhilda?
- Hm-mm.

309
00:26:04,898 --> 00:26:05,774
- Were her owners German?
- Yeah, how you know?

310
00:26:07,192 --> 00:26:07,359
She wasn't born on
the Carrucan plantation.

311
00:26:09,903 --> 00:26:10,070
She was raised by a German mistress,
the Von Shafts.

312
00:26:12,197 --> 00:26:12,364
She speak a little German, too.

313
00:26:14,116 --> 00:26:14,282
- Your wife?
- Hm-mm.

314
00:26:16,118 --> 00:26:16,284
When she was little, her mistress
taught her so she'd have somebody

315
00:26:17,869 --> 00:26:20,455
to speak German with.

316
00:26:20,622 --> 00:26:25,210
Well, let me get this straight.

317
00:26:25,377 --> 00:26:26,503
Your slave wife speaks German
and her name is Broomhilda Von Shaft?

318
00:26:30,549 --> 00:26:33,301
Yep.

319
00:26:41,893 --> 00:26:43,812
They call me Hildi.

320
00:26:49,985 --> 00:26:55,574
[Rooster crowing nearby]

321
00:26:56,908 --> 00:26:59,661
When we gain access to these
plantations, we'll be putting on an act.

322
00:27:06,543 --> 00:27:07,669
You'll be playing a character.

323
00:27:08,378 --> 00:27:09,796
Hm?

324
00:27:16,803 --> 00:27:21,266
No?

325
00:27:22,350 --> 00:27:23,893
During the act, you can
never break character.

326
00:27:24,644 --> 00:27:27,188
Do you understand?

327
00:27:29,524 --> 00:27:33,445
Yeah. Don't break character.

328
00:27:34,195 --> 00:27:35,697
And your character
is that of the valet.

329
00:27:36,615 --> 00:27:38,992
What that is?

330
00:27:39,159 --> 00:27:40,410
That's a fancy word for servant.

331
00:27:40,577 --> 00:27:41,745
- Valet?
- Hm-mm.

332
00:27:41,911 --> 00:27:46,416
[Chuckles]

333
00:27:48,835 --> 00:27:50,670
And now, Django, you may choose
your character's costume.

334
00:27:50,837 --> 00:27:51,796
Youse gonna let me
pick out my own clothes?

335
00:27:51,963 --> 00:27:55,634
But of course.

336
00:28:20,575 --> 00:28:21,785
[Medium-tempo song
resumes playing]

337
00:28:26,081 --> 00:28:29,668
Whoa.

338
00:28:29,834 --> 00:28:33,213
It's against the law for niggers
to ride horses in this territory.

339
00:28:33,380 --> 00:28:37,258
This is my valet.
My valet does not walk.

340
00:28:37,425 --> 00:28:40,220
- I said niggers on horses...
- [Schultz] His name is Django.

341
00:28:40,387 --> 00:28:43,848
He's a free man.
He can ride what he pleases.

342
00:28:44,516 --> 00:28:49,521
Not on my property.
Not around my niggers, he can't.

343
00:28:49,688 --> 00:28:52,148
My good sir,
perhaps we got off on the wrong boot.

344
00:28:52,315 --> 00:28:56,152
Allow me to unring this bell.

345
00:28:56,319 --> 00:28:58,446
My name is Dr. King Schultz.
This is my valet, Django.

346
00:28:58,613 --> 00:29:00,448
And these are our horses,
Tony and Fritz.

347
00:29:01,825 --> 00:29:01,992
- [Snorting]
- [Women giggling]

348
00:29:06,204 --> 00:29:06,371
Mr. Bennett?

349
00:29:10,333 --> 00:29:10,500
I've been led to believe that you
are a gentleman and a businessman.

350
00:29:12,419 --> 00:29:13,253
And it is for these attributes
we've ridden from Texas to Tennessee

351
00:29:17,549 --> 00:29:19,092
to parley with you now.

352
00:29:22,178 --> 00:29:22,345
I wish to purchase
one of your nigger gals.

353
00:29:24,139 --> 00:29:24,306
You and your jimmie
rode from Texas to Tennessee

354
00:29:25,974 --> 00:29:26,141
to buy one of my nigger gals?

355
00:29:28,059 --> 00:29:28,226
No appointment, no nothin'?

356
00:29:30,645 --> 00:29:30,812
Oh, I'm afraid so.

357
00:29:32,480 --> 00:29:32,647
Well, what if I was to say
I don't like you?

358
00:29:34,858 --> 00:29:35,025
Or your fancy-pants nigger?

359
00:29:36,985 --> 00:29:40,322
And I wouldn't sell you a tinker's damn.

360
00:29:42,240 --> 00:29:42,407
Now what you got to say about that?

361
00:29:45,660 --> 00:29:45,827
Mr. Bennett.

362
00:29:50,999 --> 00:29:52,417
If you are the businessman
I've been led to believe you to be,

363
00:29:53,460 --> 00:29:55,211
I have 5,000 things I might say
that could change your mind.

364
00:29:58,673 --> 00:30:00,675
[Chuckles softly]

365
00:30:01,760 --> 00:30:05,430
Well, come on inside and get
yourself somethin' cool to drink.

366
00:30:06,514 --> 00:30:13,188
Hm-mm.

367
00:30:15,148 --> 00:30:15,315
[Chuckles]

368
00:30:17,859 --> 00:30:18,026
Oh, maybe while we discuss business,

369
00:30:20,403 --> 00:30:20,570
you could provide one of
your loveliest black creatures

370
00:30:22,739 --> 00:30:22,906
to escort Django here
around your magnificent grounds.

371
00:30:24,658 --> 00:30:24,824
Oh, well, absolutely!
Uh, betina.

372
00:30:26,701 --> 00:30:26,868
- Yessir, Big Daddy?
- Uh...

373
00:30:28,370 --> 00:30:28,536
What's your jimmie's name again?

374
00:30:30,705 --> 00:30:30,872
' Django.
' Django.

375
00:30:34,084 --> 00:30:34,250
Betina, sugar, could you
take Django there

376
00:30:35,543 --> 00:30:35,710
and take him around the grounds here
and show him all the pretty stuff.

377
00:30:39,631 --> 00:30:39,798
As you please, Big Daddy.

378
00:30:43,134 --> 00:30:43,301
Oh, Mr. Bennett, I must remind you,
Django is a free man.

379
00:30:45,804 --> 00:30:45,971
He cannot be treated like a slave.
He... within the bounds of good taste,

380
00:30:48,974 --> 00:30:49,140
he must be treated
as an extension of myself.

381
00:30:53,770 --> 00:30:55,105
- Understood, Schultz. Betina, sugar?
- Yes'm?

382
00:30:57,273 --> 00:30:57,440
Django isn't a slave.
Django is a free man, you understand?

383
00:31:00,360 --> 00:31:00,527
You can't treat him like any
of the other niggers around here,

384
00:31:03,405 --> 00:31:03,571
'cause he ain't like any of the
other niggers around here. You got it?

385
00:31:06,700 --> 00:31:06,866
You want I should
treat him like white folks?

386
00:31:09,411 --> 00:31:09,911
No. That's not what I said.

387
00:31:14,416 --> 00:31:14,582
Then I don't know what you want,
Big Daddy.

388
00:31:19,045 --> 00:31:19,212
Yes, I can see that. Uh...

389
00:31:21,172 --> 00:31:21,339
What's the name of that peckerwood boy
from town that works with the glass?

390
00:31:24,092 --> 00:31:24,259
His mama work over at the lumberyard.

391
00:31:25,760 --> 00:31:25,927
- Oh, you mean Jerry.
- That's the boy's name. Jerry!

392
00:31:29,055 --> 00:31:29,222
You know Jerry, don't you, sugar?

393
00:31:32,183 --> 00:31:32,392
- Yes'm, Big Daddy.
- Well, that's it, then.

394
00:31:35,687 --> 00:31:39,149
You just treat him like you would Jerry.

395
00:31:41,860 --> 00:31:42,027
[Playing medium-tempo tune]

396
00:31:44,946 --> 00:31:46,114
That house we just left from
is the big house.

397
00:31:48,283 --> 00:31:48,450
Big Daddy call it that 'cause it's big.

398
00:31:51,953 --> 00:31:52,120
That there is the pantry.

399
00:31:54,164 --> 00:31:55,874
That's where Big Daddy
hang all his dead meat.

400
00:31:58,293 --> 00:31:58,460
Po' little squirrels.

401
00:32:00,211 --> 00:32:00,378
What you do for your Massa?

402
00:32:02,797 --> 00:32:02,964
Didn't you hear him tell you
I ain't no slave?

403
00:32:05,300 --> 00:32:07,135
- So you really free?
- Yes, I's free.

404
00:32:09,596 --> 00:32:09,763
You mean you wanna dress like that?

405
00:32:12,849 --> 00:32:13,016
- Betina, I need to ask you somethin'.
- What you want?

406
00:32:14,476 --> 00:32:14,642
I'm lookin' for three white men.
Three brothers. Overseers.

407
00:32:16,519 --> 00:32:16,686
Their name is Brittle. You know 'em?

408
00:32:20,982 --> 00:32:21,149
- Brittle?
- Yes, Brittle.

409
00:32:22,984 --> 00:32:23,568
John Brittle, Ellis Brittle,
Roger Brittle, sometime called Lil Raj.

410
00:32:25,403 --> 00:32:25,570
I don't know them.

411
00:32:27,822 --> 00:32:27,989
They could be usin' a different name.

412
00:32:30,617 --> 00:32:30,784
They woulda come to the plantation
this past year.

413
00:32:32,911 --> 00:32:33,078
- You mean the Shaffers?
- Maybe.

414
00:32:34,829 --> 00:32:34,996
- Three brothers?
- Uh-huh.

415
00:32:36,748 --> 00:32:36,915
- They here?
- Uh-huh.

416
00:32:39,209 --> 00:32:45,173
Could you point one of 'em out to me?

417
00:32:48,009 --> 00:32:53,306
Well, one's over in that field.

418
00:32:54,891 --> 00:32:55,058
[Medium-tempo song plays]

419
00:32:56,017 --> 00:32:56,184
[Django] Old man Carrucan ain't
gonna appreciate this, now.

420
00:32:58,061 --> 00:32:58,228
She work in the house, John.

421
00:33:00,188 --> 00:33:00,355
You could mess her skin up,
and you gonna mess her up

422
00:33:02,232 --> 00:33:06,820
and she ain't gonna be worth...
She ain't gonna be worth a damn thing.

423
00:33:08,988 --> 00:33:09,155
Now, your Bible say...

424
00:33:10,782 --> 00:33:10,949
[Django] Look, I told you
that I was one that made her do it.

425
00:33:13,243 --> 00:33:13,409
You ready?

426
00:33:14,786 --> 00:33:14,953
She didn't wanna run off with me. If
anybody should be gettin' whupped now,

427
00:33:17,914 --> 00:33:18,081
it should be me. It should be me, John.

428
00:33:20,667 --> 00:33:27,674
Now, I been here long enough, you know
me, you know me a long time, now.

429
00:33:29,634 --> 00:33:29,801
[Dogs barKing in distance]

430
00:33:31,427 --> 00:33:31,594
You know Massa Carrucan
ain't gonna appreciate this.

431
00:33:35,014 --> 00:33:39,102
She's a... she's a house slave.

432
00:33:41,020 --> 00:33:47,569
- She a house slave, she can't be...
- [Screaming]

433
00:33:49,904 --> 00:33:54,033
[Dogs howling]

434
00:33:56,870 --> 00:33:57,036
[Screaming]

435
00:33:58,913 --> 00:33:59,080
On my knees. I'm asKing you this,
please. Ain't this what you want?

436
00:34:01,875 --> 00:34:04,878
I'm keeping it funny for you.
Now, John, please.

437
00:34:06,004 --> 00:34:06,171
[Gasping sobbing]

438
00:34:08,131 --> 00:34:08,298
I's on my knees, John.

439
00:34:10,800 --> 00:34:12,093
I like the way you beg, boy.

440
00:34:14,429 --> 00:34:16,264
[Whip cracKing, echoing]

441
00:34:17,432 --> 00:34:18,725
Is that who you was lookin' for?

442
00:34:18,892 --> 00:34:22,645
Yep.

443
00:34:22,812 --> 00:34:24,480
Where the other two at?

444
00:34:25,106 --> 00:34:26,983
They by the stable,
punishin' little Jody for breakin' eggs.

445
00:34:27,483 --> 00:34:30,695
They whippin' little Jody?

446
00:34:35,325 --> 00:34:37,410
Point me in that direction.

447
00:34:39,037 --> 00:34:40,330
You go to that tree
and keep goin' that-a way.

448
00:34:40,496 --> 00:34:41,998
Go get that white man
I came here with.

449
00:34:42,165 --> 00:34:44,709
- [Man] Come on, now.
- No, no, please!

450
00:34:44,876 --> 00:34:47,337
- Come on, girlie.
- [Shrieks] Please!

451
00:34:47,503 --> 00:34:50,465
- Come on. Get you set up now.
- [Screaming]

452
00:34:50,632 --> 00:34:52,926
"And the lord said,
'the fear of ye..."

453
00:34:53,092 --> 00:34:54,052
- [CracKing]
- "...And the dread of ye

454
00:34:54,218 --> 00:34:55,595
shall be on every beast
of the earth."'

455
00:34:55,762 --> 00:34:58,848
[cracKing]

456
00:35:16,032 --> 00:35:17,784
Come here now, woman!

457
00:35:19,869 --> 00:35:22,163
- You'd better give me that arm!
- [Screaming]

458
00:35:31,881 --> 00:35:35,885
Ok, she's ready!

459
00:35:39,305 --> 00:35:41,224
[Whimpering]

460
00:36:01,786 --> 00:36:04,455
And after this, we'll see
if you break eggs again.

461
00:36:15,383 --> 00:36:17,760
John Brittle!

462
00:36:23,516 --> 00:36:26,060
- You remember me?
- [Metal springing noise]

463
00:36:35,111 --> 00:36:36,904
I like the way you die, boy.

464
00:36:37,530 --> 00:36:38,948
Goddamn son of a bitch!

465
00:36:39,657 --> 00:36:40,742
[Grunting]

466
00:36:44,120 --> 00:36:45,580
[Whip cracKing]

467
00:36:49,459 --> 00:36:51,169
[Groaning]

468
00:37:00,219 --> 00:37:01,804
- Keep it funny!
- [Grunting]

469
00:37:11,147 --> 00:37:12,607
[Yelling]

470
00:37:13,399 --> 00:37:14,859
[Man groaning]

471
00:37:16,110 --> 00:37:17,779
Y'all wanna see somethin'?

472
00:37:22,283 --> 00:37:23,701
[CocKing pistol]

473
00:37:27,914 --> 00:37:29,457
No! [Groans]

474
00:37:30,166 --> 00:37:33,169
[ClicKing]

475
00:37:33,336 --> 00:37:34,837
Who were they?

476
00:37:35,004 --> 00:37:37,340
That's big John,
and that's Lil Raj.

477
00:37:42,178 --> 00:37:43,679
Where's Ellis?

478
00:37:43,846 --> 00:37:45,765
He's the one hightailin' it
across that field right now.

479
00:37:45,932 --> 00:37:48,184
- You sure that's him?
- Yeah.

480
00:37:48,351 --> 00:37:49,602
- Positive?
- I don't know.

481
00:37:49,769 --> 00:37:52,063
- You don't know if you're positive?
- I don't know what "positive" mean.

482
00:38:05,284 --> 00:38:06,869
- It means you're sure.
- Yes.

483
00:38:11,916 --> 00:38:12,917
- "Yes," what?
- Yes, I'm sure that's Ellis Brittle.

484
00:38:14,710 --> 00:38:17,130
I'm positive he dead.

485
00:38:17,296 --> 00:38:19,549
Django!

486
00:38:19,715 --> 00:38:21,259
Everybody calm down.

487
00:38:21,425 --> 00:38:24,428
We mean no one else any harm.

488
00:38:24,595 --> 00:38:27,265
Who are you two jokers?

489
00:38:27,431 --> 00:38:32,019
I am Dr. King Schultz,
a legal representative

490
00:38:32,186 --> 00:38:34,147
of the criminal justice system of
the United States of America.

491
00:38:34,313 --> 00:38:38,401
The man to my left is Django Freeman.
He's my deputy.

492
00:38:38,568 --> 00:38:42,446
In my pocket is a warrant,

493
00:38:42,613 --> 00:38:47,618
signed by Circuit Court Judge
Henry Allen Laudermilk of Austin, Texas,

494
00:38:47,785 --> 00:38:49,871
for the arrest and capture,
dead or alive,

495
00:38:51,289 --> 00:38:55,418
of John Brittle,
Roger Brittle and Ellis Brittle.

496
00:38:55,585 --> 00:38:57,253
They were goin' by the name Shaffer.

497
00:38:57,420 --> 00:38:58,880
You know them by the name of Shaffer,
but the butchers' real name was Brittle.

498
00:38:59,046 --> 00:39:03,176
These are wanted men.

499
00:39:03,342 --> 00:39:06,637
The law wants 'em for murder.

500
00:39:06,804 --> 00:39:10,266
Now, I reiterate, the warrant
states dead or alive,

501
00:39:11,392 --> 00:39:15,771
so when Mr. Freeman and myself
executed these men on sight,

502
00:39:15,938 --> 00:39:19,984
we were operating
within our legal boundaries.

503
00:39:20,151 --> 00:39:22,528
I realize passions are high,

504
00:39:22,695 --> 00:39:26,616
but I must warn you,
the penalty for taKing deadly force

505
00:39:29,493 --> 00:39:34,373
against an officer of the court
in the performance of his duty

506
00:39:36,459 --> 00:39:37,585
is you'll be hung by the neck
until you're dead.

507
00:39:54,143 --> 00:39:55,478
Now, may I please remove the warrant
from my pocket so you may examine it?

508
00:40:01,984 --> 00:40:04,278
Gimme.

509
00:40:09,992 --> 00:40:12,995
Satisfied?

510
00:40:13,663 --> 00:40:18,084
May I have that back, please?

511
00:40:21,170 --> 00:40:23,631
- Get off my land.
- Posthaste.

512
00:40:43,943 --> 00:40:47,446
Load up the bodies as quickly as you can
and let's get outta here.

513
00:40:55,329 --> 00:40:58,708
[Schultz whistling indistinctly]

514
00:41:00,543 --> 00:41:04,839
Yeah, that's them sons-a-bitches.

515
00:41:12,680 --> 00:41:15,725
[Galloping hoofbeats]

516
00:41:27,486 --> 00:41:28,738
- [Dramatic choral music]
- [Horses snorting, whinnying]

517
00:41:30,948 --> 00:41:34,452
[Men yelling, whooping]

518
00:41:43,669 --> 00:41:48,090
Come on, men!

519
00:41:48,257 --> 00:41:50,468
- [Man 1] We're coming for you, nigger!
- [Man 2] Hee-haw!

520
00:41:51,218 --> 00:41:53,846
Now, unless they start shootin' first,
nobody shoot 'em.

521
00:41:54,013 --> 00:41:59,060
That's way too simple for these jokers.

522
00:42:02,938 --> 00:42:04,148
We're gonna whup that
nigger-lover to death.

523
00:42:05,483 --> 00:42:08,110
And I'm gonna personally
strip and clip that garboon myself.

524
00:42:09,028 --> 00:42:10,321
Damn.

525
00:42:10,488 --> 00:42:12,865
I can't see fuckin' shit
outta this thing.

526
00:42:13,032 --> 00:42:15,409
We ready or what?

527
00:42:15,576 --> 00:42:17,787
[Big Daddy] Aw, hold on,
I'm fuckin' with my eyeholes.

528
00:42:17,953 --> 00:42:19,997
- [Fabric ripping]
- Oh... oh, shit.

529
00:42:20,164 --> 00:42:23,125
I just made it worse.

530
00:42:23,292 --> 00:42:26,879
Who made this goddamn shit?

531
00:42:27,046 --> 00:42:29,632
- Willard's wife.
- Well, make your own goddamn masks!

532
00:42:29,799 --> 00:42:31,467
Look, nobody's sayin'
they don't appreciate what Jenny did.

533
00:42:31,634 --> 00:42:34,428
Well, if all I had to do
was cut a hole in a bag,

534
00:42:34,595 --> 00:42:35,805
I coulda cut it better than this!

535
00:42:35,971 --> 00:42:40,309
What about you, Robert?
Can you see?

536
00:42:40,476 --> 00:42:43,979
Not too good.

537
00:42:44,146 --> 00:42:46,232
I mean, if I don't move my head I can
see you pretty good, more or less.

538
00:42:46,774 --> 00:42:48,442
But when I start ridin', the bag's
movin' all over, and I'm ridin' blind.

539
00:42:49,276 --> 00:42:50,403
- Shit.
- [Man] Yeah.

540
00:42:50,569 --> 00:42:52,113
I just made mine worse.

541
00:42:52,279 --> 00:42:55,241
Oh, God.

542
00:42:55,408 --> 00:42:57,034
Anybody bring any extra bags?

543
00:42:57,201 --> 00:42:58,994
No, nobody brought an extra bag!

544
00:42:59,161 --> 00:43:00,371
I'm just askin'.

545
00:43:00,538 --> 00:43:03,624
Do we have to wear 'em when we ride?

546
00:43:03,791 --> 00:43:05,751
Oh, well, shitfire!

547
00:43:05,918 --> 00:43:08,629
If you don't wear 'em as you ride up,
that just defeats the purpose!

548
00:43:08,796 --> 00:43:11,215
Well, I can't see
in this fuckin' thing!

549
00:43:11,382 --> 00:43:15,177
I can't breathe in this fuckin' thing
and I can't ride in this fuckin' thing!

550
00:43:15,344 --> 00:43:17,346
Well, fuck all y'all! I'm goin' home!

551
00:43:17,513 --> 00:43:21,267
Now, I watched my wife work all day
gettin' 30 bags together

552
00:43:21,434 --> 00:43:24,603
for you ungrateful sons-a-bitches,

553
00:43:25,896 --> 00:43:28,774
and all I can hear is
criticize, criticize, criticize!

554
00:43:28,941 --> 00:43:32,027
From now on, don't ask me
or mine for nothin'!

555
00:43:32,194 --> 00:43:33,529
Now, look, let's not forget
why we're here.

556
00:43:33,696 --> 00:43:37,533
We got a killer nigger
over that hill there!

557
00:43:37,700 --> 00:43:42,496
And we gotta make a lesson out of him.

558
00:43:42,663 --> 00:43:43,622
Ok, I'm confused.
Are the bags on or off?

559
00:43:43,789 --> 00:43:47,877
I think we all think
the bag was a nice idea.

560
00:43:48,836 --> 00:43:52,548
- Yeah.
- [Mumbling agreements]

561
00:43:52,715 --> 00:43:57,720
But, not pointin' any fingers,
they coulda been done better.

562
00:43:57,887 --> 00:43:59,889
So how 'bout no bags this time,

563
00:44:00,055 --> 00:44:03,392
but next time we do the bags right
and then we go full regalia.

564
00:44:03,559 --> 00:44:05,561
- I like that idea a lot.
- You get my vote, Robert.

565
00:44:05,728 --> 00:44:06,812
Wait a minute!
I didn't say no bags.

566
00:44:06,979 --> 00:44:08,856
But nobody can see.

567
00:44:09,023 --> 00:44:13,777
So?

568
00:44:13,944 --> 00:44:19,325
So it'd be nice to see.

569
00:44:19,492 --> 00:44:22,286
Goddamn it! This is a raid!
I can't see, you can't see!

570
00:44:23,078 --> 00:44:24,788
So what? All that matters is can
the fuckin' horse see! That's a raid!

571
00:44:24,955 --> 00:44:28,584
- [Overlapping shouts]
- [Man] Sons of bitches!

572
00:44:29,418 --> 00:44:31,420
I can't see shit!

573
00:44:31,587 --> 00:44:33,214
[Big Daddy] There he is! Get that nigger
out from under that wagon!

574
00:44:33,380 --> 00:44:34,798
And get that nigger-lover
outta the wagon!

575
00:44:34,965 --> 00:44:36,008
That nigger ain't down here,
Big Daddy!

576
00:44:36,175 --> 00:44:37,593
- What?
- They tricked us!

577
00:44:39,053 --> 00:44:41,347
Well, where are they?

578
00:44:43,307 --> 00:44:45,100
Auf wiedersehen.

579
00:44:45,267 --> 00:44:46,310
- [All shouting]
- [Horses whinnying]

580
00:44:46,477 --> 00:44:49,146
Oh! [Chuckles]

581
00:44:49,313 --> 00:44:52,608
Bull's-eye.

582
00:44:55,236 --> 00:44:57,821
- [Men yelling]
- [Horses whinnying]

583
00:44:57,988 --> 00:44:59,949
- [Django] Look at 'em run.
- [All shouting]

584
00:45:06,080 --> 00:45:07,331
Yeah, cowards tend to do that.

585
00:45:11,961 --> 00:45:13,671
Goddamn it!

586
00:45:20,469 --> 00:45:22,304
[Big Daddy] Goddamn it!

587
00:45:22,930 --> 00:45:25,099
Would you care to?

588
00:45:27,142 --> 00:45:28,602
Can't see shit outta this!

589
00:45:28,769 --> 00:45:30,020
- He's getting away.
- I got him.

590
00:45:34,483 --> 00:45:36,986
[Schultz]
Big Daddy's getting away.

591
00:45:45,286 --> 00:45:46,328
I got him.

592
00:45:51,166 --> 00:45:54,169
- [Slow-motion impact sound]
- [Big Daddy grunting]

593
00:45:58,841 --> 00:46:00,509
Got him.

594
00:46:04,847 --> 00:46:08,642
[Chuckles] The kid's a natural.

595
00:46:08,809 --> 00:46:11,061
[Animal yipping nearby]

596
00:46:11,228 --> 00:46:13,939
How you know Broomhilda's
first masters was German?

597
00:46:14,106 --> 00:46:16,358
Broomhilda is a German name.

598
00:46:17,151 --> 00:46:20,112
If they named her,
it stands to reason they'd be German.

599
00:46:20,279 --> 00:46:24,199
Lots of gals where you're from
named Broomhilda?

600
00:46:24,366 --> 00:46:26,327
Broomhilda is the name of a character

601
00:46:26,493 --> 00:46:28,203
in the most popular
of all the German legends.

602
00:46:34,251 --> 00:46:37,713
There's a story about Broomhilda?

603
00:46:44,136 --> 00:46:45,512
Oh, yes, there is.

604
00:46:47,014 --> 00:46:53,020
- Do you know it?
- Oh, every German knows that story.

605
00:46:54,855 --> 00:46:58,942
Would you like me to tell you?

606
00:46:59,985 --> 00:47:03,197
Well, Broomhilda was a princess.

607
00:47:03,364 --> 00:47:04,615
She was a daughter of Wotan,
God of all gods.

608
00:47:05,574 --> 00:47:07,034
Anyway, her father is really mad at her.

609
00:47:07,201 --> 00:47:09,870
What she do?

610
00:47:10,037 --> 00:47:13,207
I can't exactly remember.

611
00:47:13,874 --> 00:47:15,000
She disobeys him in some way.

612
00:47:15,167 --> 00:47:16,418
So he puts her on top of the Mountain.

613
00:47:16,585 --> 00:47:19,380
Broomhilda's on a Mountain?

614
00:47:19,546 --> 00:47:23,592
It's a German legend,

615
00:47:25,260 --> 00:47:30,349
there's always going to be
a Mountain in there somewhere.

616
00:47:31,809 --> 00:47:36,146
And he puts a fire-breathing dragon
there to guard the Mountain.

617
00:47:37,439 --> 00:47:42,736
And he surrounds her
in a circle of hellfire.

618
00:47:43,821 --> 00:47:45,406
And there, Broomhilda shall remain.

619
00:47:45,572 --> 00:47:48,534
Unless a hero arises
brave enough to save her.

620
00:47:48,701 --> 00:47:50,744
Does a fella arise?

621
00:47:51,453 --> 00:47:52,454
Yes, Django, as a matter of fact,
he does.

622
00:47:54,623 --> 00:47:57,251
A fella named Siegfried.

623
00:47:58,293 --> 00:48:02,423
Does Siegfried save her?

624
00:48:03,132 --> 00:48:07,302
Quite spectacularly so.

625
00:48:07,469 --> 00:48:09,972
He scales the Mountain,
because he's not afraid of it.

626
00:48:12,307 --> 00:48:14,685
He slays the dragon,
because he's not afraid of him.

627
00:48:18,814 --> 00:48:20,482
And he walks through hellfire...

628
00:48:21,942 --> 00:48:24,820
...because Broomhilda's worth it.

629
00:48:30,325 --> 00:48:34,496
I know how he feel.

630
00:48:37,416 --> 00:48:41,462
I think I'm just
starting to realize that.

631
00:48:42,588 --> 00:48:46,175
Now, look, Django...

632
00:48:47,217 --> 00:48:51,680
...I don't doubt that one day
you'll save your lady love...

633
00:48:51,847 --> 00:48:54,725
...but I can't let you go to
Greenville in a good conscience.

634
00:48:57,686 --> 00:48:59,855
A slave auction town in Miss.issippi
isn't the place for you to visit.

635
00:49:07,362 --> 00:49:09,782
Free or not, it's just too dangerous.

636
00:49:11,283 --> 00:49:13,619
But let me ask you a question.

637
00:49:14,453 --> 00:49:15,788
How do you like the
bounty hunting business?

638
00:49:15,954 --> 00:49:18,373
Kill white folks
and they pay you for it?

639
00:49:18,540 --> 00:49:21,376
What's not to like?

640
00:49:21,543 --> 00:49:23,629
Now, I have to admit,
we make a good team.

641
00:49:23,796 --> 00:49:25,756
I thought you was mad at me
for killin' Big John and Lil Raj.

642
00:49:26,548 --> 00:49:28,759
Yeah, on that occasion
you were a tad overzealous,

643
00:49:28,926 --> 00:49:30,928
but normally, that's a good thing.

644
00:49:31,094 --> 00:49:35,390
How'd you like to partner up
for the winter?

645
00:49:36,391 --> 00:49:38,393
What you mean "partner up"?

646
00:49:39,603 --> 00:49:43,524
You work with me through the winter
till the snow melts...

647
00:49:43,690 --> 00:49:46,610
...I give you a third of my bounties.

648
00:49:46,777 --> 00:49:49,988
So we make some money this winter,
and when the snow melts,

649
00:49:54,243 --> 00:49:55,994
I'll take you to Greenville myself

650
00:49:57,746 --> 00:49:59,706
and we'll find
where they sent your wife.

651
00:49:59,873 --> 00:50:01,250
Why you care what happen to me?

652
00:50:02,543 --> 00:50:05,420
Why you care if I find my wife?

653
00:50:05,587 --> 00:50:09,424
Frankly...

654
00:50:10,676 --> 00:50:14,388
...I've never given anybody
their freedom before.

655
00:50:16,932 --> 00:50:19,810
And now that I have,
I feel vaguely responsible for you.

656
00:50:19,977 --> 00:50:22,604
Plus, when a German meets a real life
Siegfried, that's kind of a big deal.

657
00:50:29,361 --> 00:50:32,531
As a German, I'm obliged
to help you on your quest

658
00:52:31,900 --> 00:52:32,901
to rescue your beloved Broomhilda.

659
00:52:39,700 --> 00:52:44,621
[Medium-tempo song plays]

660
00:52:44,788 --> 00:52:47,499
[Man] You got her.

661
00:52:47,666 --> 00:52:49,251
Ooh. What happened to Mr. "I wanna
shoot white folks for money"?

662
00:52:49,418 --> 00:52:51,920
- His son's with him.
- Well, good.

663
00:52:53,922 --> 00:52:55,966
He'll have a loved one with him.

664
00:52:56,133 --> 00:52:58,427
Maybe even share a last word.

665
00:53:06,601 --> 00:53:07,936
That's better than most of them get.

666
00:53:10,939 --> 00:53:12,649
Damn sight better than he deserves.

667
00:53:13,442 --> 00:53:15,777
Put down the rifle.

668
00:53:19,740 --> 00:53:21,241
Don't worry, I'm not mad at you.

669
00:53:22,117 --> 00:53:23,910
Let's take out Smitty Bacall's handbill.

670
00:53:26,329 --> 00:53:28,999
Read it aloud.

671
00:53:29,958 --> 00:53:33,879
Consider that today's lesson.

672
00:53:34,046 --> 00:53:36,298
"Wanted. Dead or alive.

673
00:53:36,465 --> 00:53:40,135
Smitty Bacall and the
Smitty Bacall

674
00:53:41,553 --> 00:53:43,096
- [schultz] Gang.
- "Gang."

675
00:53:43,263 --> 00:53:46,058
"For murder and stagecoach...

676
00:53:46,224 --> 00:53:47,559
...robbery.

677
00:53:47,726 --> 00:53:51,938
- Seven-zero-zero-zero. .
- Seven thousand.

678
00:53:52,105 --> 00:53:57,194
Thousand.

679
00:53:57,360 --> 00:53:59,154
"$7,000 for Smitty Bacall.

680
00:54:00,197 --> 00:54:02,199
$1,500 for each of his...

681
00:54:02,908 --> 00:54:07,537


682
00:54:07,704 --> 00:54:09,456
- mem...
- "Members.

683
00:54:09,623 --> 00:54:13,335
Known members of the Smitty Bacall
gang are as follas:"

684
00:54:14,461 --> 00:54:16,379
- Follows.
- "Follows."

685
00:54:17,380 --> 00:54:19,633
"Dandy Michaels, Gerald Nash and..."

686
00:54:19,800 --> 00:54:22,677
Crazy Craig Koons.

687
00:54:22,844 --> 00:54:24,805
That is who Smitty Bacall is.

688
00:54:25,514 --> 00:54:28,934
If Smitty Bacall wanted
to start a farm at 22,

689
00:54:29,101 --> 00:54:31,520
they would never have printed that.

690
00:54:32,187 --> 00:54:35,524
But Smitty Bacall
wanted to rob stagecoaches

691
00:54:36,775 --> 00:54:38,235
and he didn't mind
killing people to do it.

692
00:54:38,401 --> 00:54:41,947
Do you want to save your wife
by doing what I do?

693
00:54:42,864 --> 00:54:46,660
This is what I do.

694
00:54:46,827 --> 00:54:49,037
I kill people and
sell their corpses for cash.

695
00:54:53,834 --> 00:54:55,836
This corpse is worth $7,000.

696
00:54:57,003 --> 00:54:58,380
Now quit your pussyfooting
and shoot him.

697
00:54:59,172 --> 00:55:00,549
[Horse whinnying]

698
00:55:00,715 --> 00:55:02,050
[Boy giggles]

699
00:55:10,517 --> 00:55:12,227
Pa?

700
00:55:12,394 --> 00:55:14,479
Pa!

701
00:55:14,646 --> 00:55:16,731
Here.

702
00:55:16,898 --> 00:55:19,693
You need to keep this
Smitty Bacall handbill.

703
00:55:29,452 --> 00:55:32,205
- Why?
- It's good luck.

704
00:56:07,616 --> 00:56:09,034
You always keep the handbill
of your first bounty.

705
00:56:23,715 --> 00:56:25,592
[Up-tempo guitar music plays]

706
00:56:36,311 --> 00:56:37,687
That's accurate.

707
00:56:43,693 --> 00:56:46,655
- [Horses whinny]
- [Overlapping gunshots]

708
00:57:17,352 --> 00:57:20,480
[Shell casings clinKing]

709
00:57:21,523 --> 00:57:23,692
[Bellowing]

710
00:57:23,858 --> 00:57:25,819
Doctor, Django, how the hell are ya?

711
00:57:25,986 --> 00:57:28,989
Who the hell-a you got there?

712
00:57:29,698 --> 00:57:34,244
[Schultz] The Wilson-Lowe gang.

713
00:57:34,411 --> 00:57:38,039
Who the hell is the Wilson-Lowe gang?

714
00:57:38,206 --> 00:57:40,583
Bad Chuck Wilson and meaner
Bobby Lowe and three of their acolytes.

715
00:57:40,750 --> 00:57:42,585
Huh. Well, just leave 'em out here,
they ain't going nowhere.

716
00:57:42,752 --> 00:57:45,297
Why don't you come in then
out of the snowy snow

717
00:57:45,463 --> 00:57:46,881
and get yourselves some coffee.

718
00:58:06,151 --> 00:58:08,862
We had a birthday yesterday.
Got some cake.

719
00:58:09,029 --> 00:58:11,364
Pretty good.

720
00:58:16,703 --> 00:58:18,788
[Chains rattling]

721
00:58:20,332 --> 00:58:21,583
[Man 1] Move along!

722
00:58:21,750 --> 00:58:23,710
Move it, boy!

723
00:58:25,253 --> 00:58:27,630
[Man 2] Keep movin'.

724
00:58:44,064 --> 00:58:45,315
Get on up on that auction block.

725
00:58:47,776 --> 00:58:51,696
Don't let that mud slow you down.
Keep going.

726
00:58:51,863 --> 00:58:53,281
Keep goin'!

727
00:58:54,949 --> 00:58:57,202
[Schultz]
"Broomhilda Von Shaft. Age 27.

728
00:58:57,369 --> 00:59:01,790
'R' on right cheek."

729
00:59:01,956 --> 00:59:03,291
Calvin Candie.

730
00:59:03,458 --> 00:59:04,542
He owns the fourth biggest cotton
plantation in Miss.issippi: Candyland.

731
00:59:04,709 --> 00:59:06,795
Candyland?

732
00:59:06,961 --> 00:59:09,631
Oh, so you've heard of it.

733
00:59:09,798 --> 00:59:11,466
Ain't no slave ain't heard of Candyland.

734
00:59:11,633 --> 00:59:15,178
Well, apparently,
that's where your wife is...

735
00:59:15,345 --> 00:59:17,472
- [Sighs]
- ...And that's the repellant gentleman

736
00:59:17,639 --> 00:59:19,641
who owns her. Let's just hope she
works in the house, not in the field.

737
00:59:20,308 --> 00:59:22,227
Oh, no, she ain't no field nigger.

738
00:59:23,812 --> 00:59:25,605
She... she pretty.

739
00:59:26,815 --> 00:59:28,983
And she talk good, too.

740
00:59:30,402 --> 00:59:31,569
But when they tore her back up
and then they...

741
00:59:32,195 --> 00:59:33,321
...burned that runaway "r"
on her cheek...

742
00:59:33,488 --> 00:59:35,031
...they goddamned her.

743
00:59:36,282 --> 00:59:37,659
[Yells]

744
00:59:37,826 --> 00:59:39,828
- [Sizzling]
- [Screaming]

745
00:59:39,994 --> 00:59:41,287
She ain't no field nigger
but she ain't good enough

746
00:59:41,454 --> 00:59:43,331
for the house no more either.

747
00:59:44,249 --> 00:59:45,542
They gonna try to
make her a comfort girl.

748
00:59:47,127 --> 00:59:48,920
What's a comfort...? Oh.

749
00:59:52,006 --> 00:59:53,716
Not while I got freedom.

750
00:59:56,344 --> 00:59:57,720
Not while I got my gun.

751
00:59:59,305 --> 01:00:00,974
So do we offer to buy her?

752
01:00:03,143 --> 01:00:06,354
So...

753
01:00:06,521 --> 01:00:08,565
...say...

754
01:00:09,524 --> 01:00:12,485
...a man wants to buy a horse.

755
01:00:12,652 --> 01:00:14,320
Needs to buy a horse.

756
01:00:14,487 --> 01:00:16,281
He walks up to the farmer's farm,
and he knocks on the farmer's door

757
01:00:16,448 --> 01:00:18,658
and asks the farmer to buy his horse.

758
01:00:20,160 --> 01:00:25,123
And do you know what the farmer says?

759
01:00:25,290 --> 01:00:29,419
The farmer says no.

760
01:00:29,586 --> 01:00:31,713
Well, I say fuck that farmer,
and I'm stealin' that horse.

761
01:00:31,880 --> 01:00:33,506
Fair enough. But now you're a horse
thief, and they hang horse thieves.

762
01:00:33,673 --> 01:00:37,552
Not to mention the horse
goes back to its original owner

763
01:00:37,719 --> 01:00:40,013
because the horse is still his property.

764
01:00:41,097 --> 01:00:44,684
We need her and we need a bill of sale.

765
01:00:44,851 --> 01:00:46,352
Well, if we ain't gonna try to buy her,
then how we gonna get her?

766
01:00:46,519 --> 01:00:51,065
May I offer an alternative
plan of action?

767
01:00:51,232 --> 01:00:52,775
Go ahead.

768
01:00:53,485 --> 01:00:58,531
So... the man walks up
to the farmer's farm,

769
01:00:58,698 --> 01:01:02,076
he knocks on the farmer's door...

770
01:01:02,243 --> 01:01:05,038
...and asks not to buy the horse,
but the farm.

771
01:01:05,914 --> 01:01:08,666
And makes an offer so ridiculous,

772
01:01:08,833 --> 01:01:12,086
the farmer is forced to say yes.

773
01:01:13,546 --> 01:01:15,590
- We gonna offer to buy Candyland?
- No, it's far too big.

774
01:01:15,757 --> 01:01:16,758
But apparently this farmer
ain't all about the farm.

775
01:01:16,925 --> 01:01:19,761
How much do you know
about Mandingo fighting?

776
01:01:19,928 --> 01:01:21,596
What?

777
01:01:21,763 --> 01:01:22,805
Can you convincingly
masquerade as someone

778
01:01:22,972 --> 01:01:26,601
who is an expert on Mandingo fighting?

779
01:01:26,768 --> 01:01:30,188
Why?

780
01:01:30,355 --> 01:01:34,275
[Schultz] Because my character is that
of a big money buyer from Dusseldorf,

781
01:01:34,442 --> 01:01:36,402
here in Greenville to buy my way
into the Mandingo fight game.

782
01:01:39,489 --> 01:01:40,949
And your character is a Mandingo expert
I hired to help me do it.

783
01:01:41,199 --> 01:01:43,868
[Django]
They call that "One-Eyed Charley."

784
01:01:44,035 --> 01:01:46,955
Bonjour.

785
01:01:47,121 --> 01:01:48,706
[Speaks French]

786
01:01:51,209 --> 01:01:52,669
We're here to see Mr. Calvin Candie.

787
01:01:53,711 --> 01:01:56,339
Entraz.

788
01:01:56,506 --> 01:01:59,175
- Thank you.
- Hm-mm.

789
01:01:59,342 --> 01:02:02,804
You want me to play a black slaver?

790
01:02:03,471 --> 01:02:05,598
Ain't nothin' Lower than a black slaver.

791
01:02:06,724 --> 01:02:08,726
A black slaver is Lower
than the head house nigger...

792
01:02:08,893 --> 01:02:12,939
...and, buddy,
that's pretty fuckin' low.

793
01:02:13,648 --> 01:02:15,441
Then play him that way.

794
01:02:15,608 --> 01:02:20,572
Give me your black slaver.

795
01:02:20,738 --> 01:02:23,074
[People singing
medium-tempo song]

796
01:02:24,325 --> 01:02:26,202
Â... along came the 219
toot! Toot! Peanut butter!

797
01:02:26,369 --> 01:02:29,581
[Singing continues indistinctly]

798
01:02:29,747 --> 01:02:32,542
Dr. Schultz!

799
01:02:32,709 --> 01:02:35,503
- Good to see you again!
- Mr. Moguy.

800
01:02:35,670 --> 01:02:38,506
Thank you for your assistance
in creating the opportunity

801
01:02:38,673 --> 01:02:41,092
- for this appointment.
- Nonsense, it's my job.

802
01:02:41,259 --> 01:02:43,928
So this is the One-Eyed Charley
I've heard so much about.

803
01:02:44,095 --> 01:02:46,055
Yes, this is Django Freeman.

804
01:02:46,222 --> 01:02:49,392
Django, this is Mr. Candie's lawyer,
Leonide Moguy.

805
01:02:49,559 --> 01:02:51,853
Just call me Leo.

806
01:02:52,020 --> 01:02:54,480
Calvin's in the Julius Caesar room.
You all wanna follow me?

807
01:02:54,647 --> 01:02:56,441
[Schultz] How long have you been
associated with Mr. Candie?

808
01:02:56,608 --> 01:02:59,694
[Leo] Oh, Calvin's father and I
were about 11

809
01:02:59,861 --> 01:03:02,864
when we went to
boarding school together.

810
01:03:03,031 --> 01:03:04,782
Calvin's father's father
put me through law school.

811
01:03:05,658 --> 01:03:07,076
One could almost say
I was raised to be Calvin's lawyer.

812
01:03:07,243 --> 01:03:09,996
One could almost say youse a nigger.

813
01:03:10,538 --> 01:03:14,959
What did you say?

814
01:03:15,126 --> 01:03:17,128
- I said...
- Nothing, he's just being cheeky.

815
01:03:17,295 --> 01:03:19,088
Uh, anything else about Mr. Candie
that I should know before I meet him?

816
01:03:19,255 --> 01:03:21,507
Yes, he is a bit of a Francophile.

817
01:03:21,674 --> 01:03:24,135
[Chuckles]
What civilized people aren't?

818
01:03:24,302 --> 01:03:28,306
And he prefers Monsieur Candie
to Mr. Candie.

819
01:03:29,557 --> 01:03:31,059
[Speaks French]

820
01:03:31,225 --> 01:03:33,478
He doesn't speak French. Don't speak
French to him, it'll embarrass him.

821
01:03:33,645 --> 01:03:35,146
[Men fighting, grunting]

822
01:03:35,313 --> 01:03:36,939
[Man] Get back on top, now!
Turn around!

823
01:03:38,816 --> 01:03:41,069
There you go.

824
01:03:43,905 --> 01:03:47,659
There you go.

825
01:03:48,409 --> 01:03:50,286
Why do you want to get in
the Mandingo business?

826
01:03:50,453 --> 01:03:51,788
You don't intend to allow your second
to make the proper introductions?

827
01:03:54,457 --> 01:03:57,877
Quit stalling, now.

828
01:03:58,044 --> 01:04:00,421
Answer the question.

829
01:04:05,343 --> 01:04:07,345
The awful truth? I'm bored.

830
01:04:07,512 --> 01:04:10,223
This seems like a good bit of fun.

831
01:04:12,392 --> 01:04:14,102
Well, come on over.

832
01:04:14,268 --> 01:04:15,728
We got us a fight goin' on
that's a good bit of fun.

833
01:04:15,895 --> 01:04:18,022
[Man speaks foreign language]

834
01:04:24,987 --> 01:04:26,989
Won't you accompany me to the bar?

835
01:04:36,541 --> 01:04:37,959
[Grunting, punches continue]

836
01:04:38,126 --> 01:04:39,544
You don't wear a hat in the house,
white man. Even I know that.

837
01:04:39,711 --> 01:04:42,505
- Dr. Schultz.
- What a rare pleasure.

838
01:04:42,672 --> 01:04:44,590
Keep fighting, niggers.

839
01:04:44,757 --> 01:04:48,261
- And I might add, an honor.
- Honor to meet you.

840
01:04:48,428 --> 01:04:50,722
Please have a seat,
the pleasure's all mine.

841
01:05:01,274 --> 01:05:03,860
Get free man Django here
whatever he wants.

842
01:05:07,321 --> 01:05:10,199
And I'll have sweet tea and bourbon.

843
01:05:10,366 --> 01:05:13,411
[Grunting from fighters continues]

844
01:05:13,578 --> 01:05:15,830
- [Man yelling]
- [Grunting]

845
01:05:15,997 --> 01:05:17,582
[Calvin] Use your weight, boy,
use your weight! There you go.

846
01:05:17,749 --> 01:05:20,251
He's much bigger and stronger!

847
01:05:20,418 --> 01:05:22,336
Come on, now!

848
01:05:24,338 --> 01:05:27,133
He's not doing what I told him,
for God's sakes.

849
01:05:27,300 --> 01:05:30,386
[SpeaKing foreign language]

850
01:05:30,553 --> 01:05:31,846
Come on, now, boy!
It's a fight to the death!

851
01:05:34,932 --> 01:05:37,185
- [Grunting]
- You either hit him or are you ain't?

852
01:05:38,394 --> 01:05:41,481
[Yelling]

853
01:05:41,647 --> 01:05:43,191
[SpeaKing foreign language]

854
01:05:46,986 --> 01:05:51,324
- Big Fred, come on!
- [Grunting]

855
01:05:51,491 --> 01:05:53,242
[Calvin] Turn him around! Now...

856
01:05:53,409 --> 01:05:55,203
[Calvin] Use your strength, boy!
Come on, now! Use your strength!

857
01:05:56,537 --> 01:05:58,998
[Man screaming]

858
01:06:00,082 --> 01:06:03,044
[Calvin] There you go!

859
01:06:03,211 --> 01:06:05,254
There you go! Look at that.

860
01:06:05,421 --> 01:06:06,881
See, I told you to put
some more power in there.

861
01:06:07,048 --> 01:06:09,342
Do what I told you, boy!

862
01:06:09,509 --> 01:06:12,553
- There you go!
- [Bones cracKing]

863
01:06:12,720 --> 01:06:14,806
- No!
- [Calvin] Do what I told ya!

864
01:06:14,972 --> 01:06:17,475
Blind him black, boy!
Blind him black!

865
01:06:20,686 --> 01:06:24,607
[Man screaming]

866
01:06:25,233 --> 01:06:26,400
- Oh, no, Luigi.
- [Screaming]

867
01:06:26,567 --> 01:06:29,403
- Whoo! Whoo-hoo-hoo!
- [Screaming]

868
01:06:33,533 --> 01:06:34,492
Oh...

869
01:06:34,659 --> 01:06:36,786
- [Panting]
- [Man continues screaming]

870
01:06:36,953 --> 01:06:38,246
[Playing pool]

871
01:06:42,542 --> 01:06:44,293
[Screaming continues]

872
01:06:46,003 --> 01:06:47,255
Finish him.

873
01:06:48,798 --> 01:06:50,508
Go on, boy, finish him!

874
01:06:50,675 --> 01:06:54,095
[Screaming halts]

875
01:06:54,262 --> 01:06:56,472
[Moguy] That's why they
call him big Fred.

876
01:06:56,639 --> 01:06:59,642
- Worth every penny.
- Well, arrivederci, Luigi.

877
01:07:00,268 --> 01:07:01,978
Come on up, now, boy.
Get yourself a rest.

878
01:07:23,082 --> 01:07:24,292
You did a fine job.
A real fine job.

879
01:07:34,302 --> 01:07:35,803
Mercedes.

880
01:07:37,972 --> 01:07:39,473
Tequila.

881
01:07:41,893 --> 01:07:43,561
What's your name?

882
01:07:45,688 --> 01:07:49,734
Django.

883
01:07:51,235 --> 01:07:52,737
Can you spell it?

884
01:07:52,904 --> 01:07:54,488
D-j-a-n-g-o.

885
01:08:01,203 --> 01:08:02,288
The d is silent.

886
01:08:02,455 --> 01:08:05,958
I know.

887
01:08:06,125 --> 01:08:07,835
[Speaks foreign language]

888
01:08:08,002 --> 01:08:10,588
[Calvin] Mr. Moguy, want you to
take care of my new boy here.

889
01:08:10,755 --> 01:08:13,507
You find him a room
with a soft bed,

890
01:08:13,674 --> 01:08:14,675
then you bring him up
a pony to lick his pole.

891
01:08:14,842 --> 01:08:18,721
But you be ready to travel to Candyland
tomorrow morning, now, ya hear?

892
01:08:22,558 --> 01:08:25,561
Yessir, Monsieur Candie.

893
01:08:25,728 --> 01:08:27,021
Before you go,
Roscoe, get Fred here a tall beer.

894
01:08:36,530 --> 01:08:40,326
You enjoy that, boy.
You've earned it.

895
01:08:40,493 --> 01:08:41,702
Yessir.

896
01:08:43,871 --> 01:08:45,498
- What's your name, boy?
- His name is Django Freeman.

897
01:08:45,665 --> 01:08:48,918
[Calvin chuckles]

898
01:08:50,628 --> 01:08:52,713
Where'd you dig him up?

899
01:08:53,464 --> 01:08:56,217
A fortuitous turn of events
brought Django and myself together.

900
01:08:56,384 --> 01:08:58,511
I've heard tell about you.

901
01:08:58,678 --> 01:09:02,890
I heard you been telling everybody
them Mandingos ain't no damn good.

902
01:09:04,850 --> 01:09:07,269
Ain't nothin' nobody
is sellin' is worth buyin'.

903
01:09:10,564 --> 01:09:12,650
I'm curious... what makes you
such a Mandingo expert?

904
01:09:13,693 --> 01:09:15,027
I'm curious what makes you so curious.

905
01:09:15,861 --> 01:09:17,071
- What did you say, boy?
- Calm down, Butch.

906
01:09:17,238 --> 01:09:18,948
No offense given...

907
01:09:19,115 --> 01:09:22,618
...none taken.

908
01:09:22,785 --> 01:09:24,245
[Schultz] Monsieur Candie...

909
01:09:24,870 --> 01:09:27,999
...I'd appreciate if you could
direct your line of inquiry toward me.

910
01:09:28,165 --> 01:09:31,002
One...

911
01:09:31,168 --> 01:09:33,004
...you do not have anything to drink.
Can I get you a tasty refreshment?

912
01:09:33,170 --> 01:09:35,006
- Yes! I'll have a beer.
- Wunderbar.

913
01:09:35,172 --> 01:09:37,258
Roscoe, a beer
for the man with the beard,

914
01:09:37,425 --> 01:09:40,928
and I will have a
Polynesian Pearl Diver.

915
01:09:41,095 --> 01:09:42,805
Do not spare the rum.

916
01:09:42,972 --> 01:09:48,102
Doc... I am a seasoned slaver.

917
01:09:49,562 --> 01:09:52,773
You are, well, you are a neophyte.

918
01:09:53,482 --> 01:09:55,359
I'm simply tryin' to ascertain if this
cowboy here is takin' advantage of you.

919
01:09:55,526 --> 01:09:57,653
With all due respect, Monsieur Candie...

920
01:09:57,820 --> 01:10:00,364
...I didn't seek you
out for your advice.

921
01:10:00,531 --> 01:10:03,075
I sought you out to
purchase a fighting nigger

922
01:10:03,242 --> 01:10:05,619
at above top-dollar market price.

923
01:10:08,330 --> 01:10:10,791
Now I was under the impression,
when you granted me an audience,

924
01:10:10,958 --> 01:10:13,294
it would be to discuss business.

925
01:10:15,588 --> 01:10:16,589
Well, we weren't talkin' business yet.

926
01:10:16,756 --> 01:10:19,467
We were discussin' my curiosity.

927
01:10:21,469 --> 01:10:24,930
Thank you.

928
01:10:25,097 --> 01:10:26,640
[Calvin] Roscoe, Coco,
go outside and play.

929
01:10:28,392 --> 01:10:30,895
Sheba... you stay right there.

930
01:10:31,812 --> 01:10:35,608
I know you didn't mean me.

931
01:10:35,775 --> 01:10:37,818
- Prost!
- German.

932
01:10:37,985 --> 01:10:40,404
Now, according to Moguy,
if I do business with you,

933
01:10:40,571 --> 01:10:44,325
I'm doing business with both y'all.

934
01:10:44,492 --> 01:10:45,659
He does the eyeballin',
you the billfold? Is that it?

935
01:10:46,952 --> 01:10:47,953
Well, you don't make it sound
too flattering, but more or less, yeah.

936
01:10:48,120 --> 01:10:50,039
Hm.

937
01:10:50,206 --> 01:10:52,166
So...

938
01:10:52,333 --> 01:10:54,502
...bright boy...

939
01:10:54,668 --> 01:10:56,170
...Moguy tells me
you looked over my African flesh

940
01:10:58,339 --> 01:11:00,382
and you was
none too impressed, huh?

941
01:11:00,549 --> 01:11:02,676
Not for top dollar.

942
01:11:02,843 --> 01:11:05,096
Well, then,
we got nothin' more to talk about.

943
01:11:05,262 --> 01:11:07,223
You see, you wanna buy
a beat-ass nigger from me,

944
01:11:08,182 --> 01:11:11,352
those are the beat-ass niggers
I wanna sell so...

945
01:11:11,519 --> 01:11:15,815
He don't wanna buy the niggers
you wanna sell.

946
01:11:18,067 --> 01:11:21,737
He wants the nigger
you don't wanna sell.

947
01:11:21,904 --> 01:11:24,323
Well, I don't sell the niggers
I don't wanna sell.

948
01:11:24,490 --> 01:11:28,160
Well, you won't sell your best.

949
01:11:28,327 --> 01:11:32,248
You won't even sell your second best.

950
01:11:33,040 --> 01:11:35,084
But your third best...?
You don't want to sell him either.

951
01:11:37,419 --> 01:11:39,713
But if I made you an offer so ridiculous
you'd be forced to consider it...

952
01:11:40,714 --> 01:11:44,802
[Chortles]
...Who knows what could happen?

953
01:11:46,554 --> 01:11:48,597
And what do you consider ridiculous?

954
01:11:51,976 --> 01:11:53,686
For a truly talented specimen,
the right nigger?

955
01:11:54,395 --> 01:11:56,063
How much would you say, Django?

956
01:11:58,232 --> 01:12:02,236
Twelve thousand dollars.

957
01:12:02,403 --> 01:12:04,321
[Straw slurping]

958
01:12:18,002 --> 01:12:23,674
Well, gentlemen, you had my curiosity,

959
01:12:23,841 --> 01:12:26,260
but now you have my attention.

960
01:12:26,427 --> 01:12:30,347
Willie. Willie.
Hold up! Hold up. Ah!

961
01:12:30,514 --> 01:12:33,392
- Good morning, gentlemen.
- Good Dr. Schultz.

962
01:12:33,559 --> 01:12:35,102
- Beautiful morning, isn't it?
- You couldn't have picked a better one.

963
01:12:35,269 --> 01:12:37,396
Please, won't you take a ride with us
here in the Victoria.

964
01:12:45,613 --> 01:12:46,906
[Schultz]
Oh, thank you very much.

965
01:12:51,702 --> 01:12:55,331
You can tie your horse up back there.

966
01:12:55,497 --> 01:13:00,669
[Calvin] Django.

967
01:13:00,836 --> 01:13:04,965
Where I part company from many
of my phrenologist colleagues

968
01:13:05,132 --> 01:13:09,803
is I believe there is a level
above bright, above talented,

969
01:13:09,970 --> 01:13:11,472
above loyal that a nigger can aspire to.

970
01:13:12,473 --> 01:13:14,516
Say, one nigger that
just pops up in 10,000.

971
01:13:15,643 --> 01:13:16,810
The exceptional nigger.

972
01:13:17,978 --> 01:13:19,855
Bright day, huh, bright boy?

973
01:13:24,610 --> 01:13:27,529
Sun is up.

974
01:13:27,696 --> 01:13:28,989
Shining on all of us.

975
01:13:29,156 --> 01:13:30,866
- [Calvin] Have a seat, doc.
- [Schultz] Thank you.

976
01:13:31,033 --> 01:13:34,411
Quite an honor.

977
01:13:34,578 --> 01:13:37,539
- The honor is all ours.
- Thank you.

978
01:13:38,499 --> 01:13:40,334
[Calvin] But I do believe that,
given time,

979
01:13:41,585 --> 01:13:43,212
exceptional niggers
like bright boy here...

980
01:13:44,964 --> 01:13:49,551
...become if not frequent...

981
01:13:49,718 --> 01:13:52,596
...more frequent.

982
01:13:53,180 --> 01:13:55,266
Bright boy,
you are that one in 10,000.

983
01:14:05,484 --> 01:14:06,860
The name of the game is keep up,
not catch up, nigger.

984
01:14:08,362 --> 01:14:11,782
[Men laughing]

985
01:14:11,949 --> 01:14:13,867
- Whoa!
- [Whinnying]

986
01:14:14,034 --> 01:14:15,077
- Touch your guns, you die.
- Everybody, calm down!

987
01:14:15,244 --> 01:14:17,246
Now I saw the whole thing.
No harm done.

988
01:14:17,413 --> 01:14:19,957
Are you kidding me?

989
01:14:21,041 --> 01:14:23,836
- This nigger just...
- I said no harm done!

990
01:14:25,045 --> 01:14:28,048
Now take your hand off your pistol!

991
01:14:29,550 --> 01:14:31,760
Butch, that means you too.

992
01:14:32,511 --> 01:14:34,054
Everybody stop antagonizing my guest.

993
01:14:34,221 --> 01:14:38,517
Hoot! Get back up on your horse.

994
01:14:38,684 --> 01:14:41,729
He broke my collarbone!

995
01:14:43,105 --> 01:14:43,272
For God's sake, somebody please help
Hoot here back up on his goddamn horse.

996
01:14:45,733 --> 01:14:45,900
- [Man] Yessir, boss.
- Oh, now you are one lucky nigger.

997
01:14:47,693 --> 01:14:48,527
You better listen to your boss,
white boy.

998
01:14:50,154 --> 01:14:50,321
Oh, I'm gonna go
walKing in the moonlight with you.

999
01:14:52,323 --> 01:14:52,490
You wanna hold my hand?

1000
01:14:54,116 --> 01:14:54,283
[Chuckling]

1001
01:14:56,953 --> 01:14:59,205
[Rap song playing]

1002
01:15:01,207 --> 01:15:07,588
[ClucKing]

1003
01:15:08,839 --> 01:15:16,839
Willie, take us home.

1004
01:15:56,012 --> 01:15:56,178
[Man] Start moving!

1005
01:15:57,430 --> 01:15:57,596
Head 'em out!

1006
01:15:59,098 --> 01:16:00,307
You got a problem
with your eyeball, boy?

1007
01:16:01,267 --> 01:16:01,434
No, sir.

1008
01:16:04,478 --> 01:16:04,645
You want a boot heel in it?

1009
01:16:07,773 --> 01:16:07,940
No, sir.

1010
01:16:09,483 --> 01:16:10,026
Then you keep your
goddamn eyeballs off me.

1011
01:16:11,444 --> 01:16:11,610
You flash that bad look at me again,
I'll give you a reason not to like me.

1012
01:16:13,738 --> 01:16:13,904
Now move, nigger!

1013
01:16:15,781 --> 01:16:15,948
[Horse snorting]

1014
01:16:19,535 --> 01:16:19,702
You niggers are gonna
understand something about me.

1015
01:16:22,747 --> 01:16:22,913
I'm worse than any of these
white men here.

1016
01:16:24,248 --> 01:16:26,751
You get the molasses out your ass,
you keep your goddamn eyeballs off me.

1017
01:16:30,129 --> 01:16:30,296
He is a rambunctious sort,
ain't he? [Chuckles]

1018
01:16:34,008 --> 01:16:34,175
Indeed.

1019
01:16:37,261 --> 01:16:37,428
May we stop for a moment
so I may put a word in my man's ear?

1020
01:16:41,807 --> 01:16:44,769
You know, I'm expecting to fall in love
once I see the specimens at Candyland,

1021
01:16:46,604 --> 01:16:46,771
so before that moment,
it would be good if I could have

1022
01:16:48,814 --> 01:16:52,860
a confidential strategy meeting
with my confidant.

1023
01:16:55,446 --> 01:16:55,613
You mind telling me
what the hell you doing?

1024
01:16:58,991 --> 01:16:59,158
I confirmed that Broomhilda's
at Candyland.

1025
01:17:01,035 --> 01:17:01,202
- You're sure it's her?
- He didn't call her by name,

1026
01:17:03,662 --> 01:17:03,829
but she's a young lady, whip marks
on her back and speaks German.

1027
01:17:08,459 --> 01:17:08,626
Now, while it's not wise to assume,

1028
01:17:10,586 --> 01:17:10,753
in this instance,
I think it's pretty safe.

1029
01:17:12,546 --> 01:17:12,713
Point being, don't get so
carried away with your retribution.

1030
01:17:15,216 --> 01:17:15,382
You lose sight of why we're here.

1031
01:17:20,346 --> 01:17:20,513
- You think I lost sight of that?
- Yes, I do.

1032
01:17:25,184 --> 01:17:25,351
Stop antagonizing Candie.

1033
01:17:28,354 --> 01:17:28,521
You're going to blow this whole charade,
or more than likely get us both killed.

1034
01:17:31,065 --> 01:17:32,066
And I, for one, don't intend to die
in Chickasaw County, Miss.issippi, USA.

1035
01:17:37,488 --> 01:17:37,655
I'm not antagonizing him.
I'm intriguing him.

1036
01:17:39,448 --> 01:17:40,866
You're yelling abuse
at these poor slaves.

1037
01:17:41,992 --> 01:17:44,245
I recall the man who had me
kill another man in front of his son

1038
01:17:45,579 --> 01:17:45,746
and he didn't bat a eye.

1039
01:17:49,208 --> 01:17:50,167
You remember that?

1040
01:17:52,169 --> 01:17:53,170
Yeah, of course I remember.

1041
01:17:56,048 --> 01:17:59,718
What you said was that
this is my world...

1042
01:18:02,888 --> 01:18:04,348
...and in my world you gotta get dirty.

1043
01:18:06,433 --> 01:18:06,934
So that's what I'm doing.
I'm gettin' dirty.

1044
01:18:08,102 --> 01:18:10,187
Well, you're paraphrasing a tad, but...

1045
01:18:11,689 --> 01:18:19,405
...that was the general gist.

1046
01:18:21,991 --> 01:18:23,284
[Sighing]

1047
01:18:25,327 --> 01:18:33,327
See you at Candyland.

1048
01:18:36,797 --> 01:18:44,797
[Django]
All right, niggers, back at it.

1049
01:19:04,116 --> 01:19:12,116
That means you too, moonlight.

1050
01:19:15,586 --> 01:19:15,753
[Dogs barKing nearby]

1051
01:19:19,006 --> 01:19:19,173
[Dogs barKing loudly]

1052
01:19:21,258 --> 01:19:21,425
[Calvin] I'll be. D'Artagnan!

1053
01:19:22,718 --> 01:19:22,885
Now, boy, why do a
fool thing like run off?

1054
01:19:26,430 --> 01:19:26,597
I can't fight no more, Monsieur Candie.

1055
01:19:29,016 --> 01:19:29,183
[Calvin] Yes, you can.

1056
01:19:31,810 --> 01:19:31,977
You might not be able to win,
but your ass can fight.

1057
01:19:34,021 --> 01:19:34,188
Mr. Stonesipher, would you please
shut these goddamn dogs up?

1058
01:19:35,731 --> 01:19:35,898
- I cannot hear myself think!
- Quiet down, Marsha!

1059
01:19:38,525 --> 01:19:38,692
Marsha, hush up! Marsha!

1060
01:19:40,945 --> 01:19:48,035
Hush up! Hey!

1061
01:19:51,497 --> 01:19:51,664
Get these goddamn dogs
away from this nigger!

1062
01:19:53,332 --> 01:19:53,874
[Dogs whining]

1063
01:19:55,542 --> 01:19:59,797
Come on now, boy...
Get on out that tree.

1064
01:20:01,173 --> 01:20:09,173
Yessir.

1065
01:20:18,023 --> 01:20:18,190
[Dogs resume barKing]

1066
01:20:21,443 --> 01:20:21,610
[BarKing stops]

1067
01:20:23,237 --> 01:20:24,363
How long was he loose?

1068
01:20:25,906 --> 01:20:26,073
[Speech slurred]
A night. Day.

1069
01:20:27,783 --> 01:20:27,950
Half the other night.

1070
01:20:30,077 --> 01:20:30,244
How far he get off the property?

1071
01:20:31,620 --> 01:20:32,871
'Bout 20 Miles off the prop.

1072
01:20:36,208 --> 01:20:36,375
Pretty far considering
that limp he got.

1073
01:20:38,002 --> 01:20:39,169
Hm.

1074
01:20:41,880 --> 01:20:42,047
Mr. Moguy, who was D'Artagnan
supposed to fight on Friday?

1075
01:20:44,550 --> 01:20:44,717
One-a this new lot.

1076
01:20:46,218 --> 01:20:46,385
Well, way he looks now, a blind Indian
wouldn't bet a bead on him.

1077
01:20:48,804 --> 01:20:48,971
[D'Artagnan weeping] Please, Monsieur
Candie, I ain't got it in me no more.

1078
01:20:51,432 --> 01:20:54,893
- Now, now, now, now, now.
- I can't...

1079
01:20:57,438 --> 01:21:00,357
Now, no beggin'.

1080
01:21:03,902 --> 01:21:04,069
No playin' on my soft heart.

1081
01:21:08,949 --> 01:21:09,116
- You in trouble now, son.
- Yessir.

1082
01:21:11,493 --> 01:21:11,660
I done paid $500 for you.

1083
01:21:15,539 --> 01:21:15,706
When I pay $500, then I expect
to get five fights out of a nigger

1084
01:21:18,417 --> 01:21:18,584
- 'fore he roll over and play dead.
- Sir.

1085
01:21:20,085 --> 01:21:20,252
You got to understand
that I'm runnin' a business here.

1086
01:21:23,255 --> 01:21:23,422
- You fought three fights.
- But I won every one.

1087
01:21:24,465 --> 01:21:27,134
Yes, you did. Yes, you did.

1088
01:21:29,178 --> 01:21:29,345
But that last one, you muddled the line
between winnin' and losin'.

1089
01:21:32,973 --> 01:21:33,140
Yessir.

1090
01:21:35,684 --> 01:21:37,561
Still, the fact remains:

1091
01:21:39,480 --> 01:21:41,023
I pay $500, I want five goddamn fights!

1092
01:21:47,029 --> 01:21:49,406
So what about my $500, huh?

1093
01:21:49,573 --> 01:21:51,617
What about my $500?

1094
01:21:53,410 --> 01:21:55,913
You gonna reimburse me?

1095
01:21:57,915 --> 01:21:59,625
You even know what "reimburse" means?

1096
01:22:03,379 --> 01:22:04,588
- [Laughing]
- [Calvin] Huh?

1097
01:22:05,798 --> 01:22:07,341
[Laughter continues]

1098
01:22:10,094 --> 01:22:12,805
I'll reimburse you!

1099
01:22:12,972 --> 01:22:16,433
You will?

1100
01:22:16,600 --> 01:22:17,726
Yep.

1101
01:22:19,979 --> 01:22:22,064
You'll pay $500

1102
01:22:22,982 --> 01:22:24,942
for practically a One-Eyed old Joe
ain't fit to push a broom?

1103
01:22:25,109 --> 01:22:27,570
No, he won't.

1104
01:22:27,736 --> 01:22:29,530
He just tired of you
toyin' with him is all.

1105
01:22:31,282 --> 01:22:32,491
Matter of fact, so am I.

1106
01:22:41,667 --> 01:22:45,421
But we ain't payin' a penny
for that pickaninny.

1107
01:22:45,588 --> 01:22:49,258
Ain't got no use for him.
Ain't that right, doc?

1108
01:22:50,050 --> 01:22:52,011
You heard him.

1109
01:22:54,263 --> 01:22:55,723
You're gonna have to excuse
Mr. Stonesipher's slack-jawed gaze.

1110
01:22:56,724 --> 01:22:58,058
He ain't never seen a
nigger like you ever in his life.

1111
01:22:59,351 --> 01:23:00,936
Ain't that right, Mr. Stonesipher?

1112
01:23:07,026 --> 01:23:08,193
That right.

1113
01:23:09,361 --> 01:23:12,489
[Calvin] For that matter...

1114
01:23:14,992 --> 01:23:18,329
...nor have I.

1115
01:23:19,455 --> 01:23:20,998
Now...

1116
01:23:24,752 --> 01:23:26,837
...seein' as you won't pay a penny
for this pickaninny here...

1117
01:23:27,630 --> 01:23:31,592
...you won't mind me handlin'
this nigger any way I see fit?

1118
01:23:31,759 --> 01:23:36,555
He's your nigger.

1119
01:23:38,015 --> 01:23:40,225
Mr. Stonesipher?

1120
01:23:41,268 --> 01:23:43,771
Let Marsha and her bitches
send D'Artagnan to nigger heaven.

1121
01:23:43,938 --> 01:23:45,356
- Marsha! Marsha, hey, get him!
- [Barks echoing]

1122
01:23:50,569 --> 01:23:53,197
Get 'im, get 'im!

1123
01:24:13,717 --> 01:24:15,761
- Yeah!
- Whoo!

1124
01:24:15,928 --> 01:24:18,097
Whoo-ee!

1125
01:24:18,263 --> 01:24:22,893
- [Dogs snarling]
- [Screaming]

1126
01:24:23,477 --> 01:24:24,770
Your boss looks a little
green around the gills

1127
01:24:25,854 --> 01:24:27,231
for a blood sport like nigger fighting.

1128
01:24:27,398 --> 01:24:30,359
Nah, he just ain't used to seein'
a man ripped apart by dogs is all.

1129
01:24:30,526 --> 01:24:35,239
Hm.

1130
01:24:35,406 --> 01:24:37,032
You are used to it?

1131
01:24:37,199 --> 01:24:40,577
I'm just a little more
used to Americans than he is.

1132
01:24:40,744 --> 01:24:42,371
- Hm.
- Now, Monsieur Candie...

1133
01:24:43,580 --> 01:24:47,960
...whenever you're ready.

1134
01:24:50,170 --> 01:24:51,588
We rode five hours
so you could show off your stock.

1135
01:25:04,059 --> 01:25:05,894
Let's get to it.

1136
01:25:11,734 --> 01:25:13,152
'Cause as of now,
if he's an example, I ain't impressed.

1137
01:25:13,318 --> 01:25:14,528
Follow me.

1138
01:26:48,872 --> 01:26:51,583
[Snarling]

1139
01:26:53,210 --> 01:26:54,586
[ClucKing]

1140
01:26:55,754 --> 01:26:57,047
[Nickering]

1141
01:26:57,214 --> 01:26:59,800
Line 'em up to the left here now, boy.

1142
01:26:59,967 --> 01:27:01,593
Stand up straight, now!

1143
01:27:01,760 --> 01:27:03,846
Get up there.

1144
01:28:01,570 --> 01:28:02,779
Get up there, boy. Come on.

1145
01:28:03,488 --> 01:28:05,115
Give me a line! Give me a line!

1146
01:28:05,282 --> 01:28:07,951
Get in line there! Straighten up!

1147
01:28:08,118 --> 01:28:11,079
[Indistinct chatter]

1148
01:28:11,246 --> 01:28:14,583
Hello! Stephen, my boy!

1149
01:28:14,750 --> 01:28:17,127
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Hello, my ass.

1150
01:28:17,294 --> 01:28:20,839
Who this nigger up on that nag?

1151
01:28:21,006 --> 01:28:24,927
Stephen, you have nails for breakfast?
What's-a matter? Why you so ornery?

1152
01:28:25,093 --> 01:28:28,931
- You Miss. me, huh?
- Oh, yessir. [Laughs]

1153
01:28:29,097 --> 01:28:31,183
I Miss. you like a hog Miss. slop!

1154
01:28:31,350 --> 01:28:35,812
- Like a baby Miss. mammy's titty.
- [All chuckling]

1155
01:28:35,979 --> 01:28:37,648
I Miss. you like I Miss.es
a rock in my shoe.

1156
01:28:38,857 --> 01:28:42,444
[Laughing]

1157
01:28:42,611 --> 01:28:45,447
Now, I axed you:
Who this nigger on that nag?

1158
01:28:45,614 --> 01:28:47,282
Hey, Snowball?

1159
01:28:47,449 --> 01:28:48,825
Wanna know my name or
the name of my horse, you ask me.

1160
01:28:48,992 --> 01:28:51,078
Just who the hell you callin'
"Snowball," horse boy?

1161
01:28:51,245 --> 01:28:55,540
I'll snatch your
black ass off that nag there

1162
01:28:55,707 --> 01:28:58,085
- and in the mud so fast...
- Whoa, whoa, whoa!

1163
01:28:58,252 --> 01:29:00,504
- ...make your head spin.
- Stephen, Stephen, Stephen.

1164
01:29:00,671 --> 01:29:04,466
Let's keep it funny.
Django here's a free man.

1165
01:29:04,633 --> 01:29:07,886
- This nigger here?
- That nigger there.

1166
01:29:08,053 --> 01:29:12,057
Let me at least
introduce the two of you.

1167
01:29:12,224 --> 01:29:16,144
Django, this is another cheeky
black bugger like yourself, Stephen.

1168
01:29:16,311 --> 01:29:17,688
Stephen, this here's Django.
You two oughta hate each other.

1169
01:29:17,854 --> 01:29:21,358
Calvin, just who the hell is this nigger
you feels the need to entertain?

1170
01:29:21,525 --> 01:29:23,902
Django and his friend in gray here,
Dr. Schultz, are customers.

1171
01:29:24,069 --> 01:29:25,737
And they are our guests, Stephen.

1172
01:29:25,904 --> 01:29:28,532
And you, you old decrepit bastard,
oughta show them every hospitality.

1173
01:29:29,533 --> 01:29:31,034
- You understand that?
- Yessir. Him I understand.

1174
01:29:31,201 --> 01:29:33,662
But I don't know why
I got to take lip off this nigger.

1175
01:29:33,829 --> 01:29:35,956
You don't have to know why.
Do you understand?

1176
01:29:37,124 --> 01:29:38,792
Yessir. I understand.

1177
01:29:38,959 --> 01:29:41,169
Well,good.
They're spendin' the night.

1178
01:29:41,336 --> 01:29:43,922
Go up in the guest bedrooms
and get two ready.

1179
01:29:44,089 --> 01:29:46,383
He gonna stay in the big house?

1180
01:29:46,550 --> 01:29:48,593
Stephen, he's a slaver.
It's different.

1181
01:29:48,760 --> 01:29:51,096
- In the big house?
- Well, you got a problem with that?

1182
01:29:51,263 --> 01:29:53,515
Oh, no.
I ain't got no problem with it,

1183
01:29:53,682 --> 01:29:55,892
if you ain't got no problem
with burnin' the bed, the sheets,

1184
01:29:56,059 --> 01:29:57,978
the pillowcases, everything else when
this black-ass motherfucker's gone!

1185
01:29:58,145 --> 01:29:59,771
That is my problem!
They are mine to burn!

1186
01:30:01,898 --> 01:30:03,817
Now your problem right now
is makin' a good impression!

1187
01:30:05,277 --> 01:30:06,445
And I want you to start solvin'
that problem right now

1188
01:30:07,362 --> 01:30:09,781
and get them goddamn rooms ready!

1189
01:30:09,948 --> 01:30:11,283
Yessir, Monsieur Candie.

1190
01:30:11,450 --> 01:30:14,995
Go on, now.

1191
01:30:15,162 --> 01:30:16,330
Can't believe you brought
a nigger to stay in the big house.

1192
01:30:16,496 --> 01:30:21,168
Your daddy rollin' over
in his goddamned grave.

1193
01:30:21,335 --> 01:30:24,421
Man, the lip on him. Whoo!
He's gettin' worse and worse.

1194
01:30:24,588 --> 01:30:29,634
Now...

1195
01:30:29,801 --> 01:30:33,805
Where is my beautiful sister?!

1196
01:30:35,057 --> 01:30:38,435
There she is!
Whoo-hoo-hoo-hoo!

1197
01:30:38,602 --> 01:30:41,980
Dr. Schultz, this attractive
Southern belle is my widowed sister.

1198
01:30:42,147 --> 01:30:44,274
Darlin', you are a tonic for tired eyes.

1199
01:30:44,441 --> 01:30:45,484
May I present to you
Lara Lee Candie-Fitzwilly.

1200
01:30:45,650 --> 01:30:47,402
Chester, Rodney, chicken charly.
Y'all get your ass over by that pen.

1201
01:30:48,612 --> 01:30:51,365
- Come on, Charly. Come on, now!
- Let's go.

1202
01:30:52,074 --> 01:30:55,077
You know where it is.

1203
01:30:55,243 --> 01:30:59,039
Like you on a rope!

1204
01:30:59,206 --> 01:31:00,165
Niggers don't walk around here,
niggers run!

1205
01:31:00,332 --> 01:31:03,335
- Monsieur Candie?
- Hm?

1206
01:31:03,502 --> 01:31:06,088
Yeah. About that matter about the
nigger girl you were talKing about?

1207
01:31:06,254 --> 01:31:10,425
Nigger gal?

1208
01:31:10,592 --> 01:31:14,763
Yeah, I believe you mentioned
she spoke German.

1209
01:31:14,930 --> 01:31:18,308
Ah, yes! Hildi, what about her?

1210
01:31:18,475 --> 01:31:20,310
Do you think before the demonstration,
you could send her around to my room?

1211
01:31:20,477 --> 01:31:21,895
[Laughs] You little dickens, you.
I don't see why not.

1212
01:31:22,062 --> 01:31:23,730
Stephen, when you get through showin'
them to their rooms, go fetch Hildi,

1213
01:31:23,897 --> 01:31:26,566
get her cleaned up
and smellin' real nice,

1214
01:31:26,775 --> 01:31:30,445
