- Hm-mm.

1338
01:43:07,517 --> 01:43:09,560
And that is a nigger
that can win fights.

1339
01:43:09,727 --> 01:43:13,689
Hm-mm.

1340
01:43:13,856 --> 01:43:16,400
Now that should be your first, second,
third, fourth, and fifth concern.

1341
01:43:16,567 --> 01:43:18,027
Now, after you have that,
and you know you have that,

1342
01:43:22,865 --> 01:43:24,492
then you can start
to implement a grand design.

1343
01:43:25,701 --> 01:43:29,080
In other words, first thing is first.

1344
01:43:29,247 --> 01:43:31,124
First thing's first.

1345
01:43:31,874 --> 01:43:34,544
[Whispers in German]

1346
01:43:34,710 --> 01:43:38,047
Ooh! I see you two gettin' on.

1347
01:43:38,214 --> 01:43:40,049
Famously.

1348
01:43:40,216 --> 01:43:42,301
Oh, Monsieur Candie,
you can't imagine what it's like

1349
01:43:42,468 --> 01:43:44,512
not to hear your
native tongue in four years.

1350
01:43:44,679 --> 01:43:47,473
Well, hell,
I can't imagine two weeks in Boston.

1351
01:43:47,640 --> 01:43:49,350
[Laughing]

1352
01:43:49,517 --> 01:43:54,730
Two weeks in Boston!

1353
01:43:54,897 --> 01:43:58,985
- Monsieur Candie, you a mess!
- [Coughing]

1354
01:43:59,152 --> 01:44:01,028
[Stephen] Two weeks in Boston!

1355
01:44:01,195 --> 01:44:02,530
I can't express the joy I felt
conversing in my mother tongue.

1356
01:44:02,697 --> 01:44:03,948
And Hildi is a charming
conversation companion.

1357
01:44:04,115 --> 01:44:06,200
[Calvin] Well, be careful now,
Dr. Schultz.

1358
01:44:06,367 --> 01:44:08,369
You might-a caught yourself

1359
01:44:08,536 --> 01:44:10,163
