01:48:35,845 --> 01:48:36,012
seein' as how they don't have
many niggers where he come from.

1444
01:48:38,389 --> 01:48:38,556
Dr. Schultz,
when you was alone with Hildi, here,

1445
01:48:40,349 --> 01:48:40,516
did you just speak German
or did you get to take her clothes off?

1446
01:48:42,560 --> 01:48:42,727
No, we just talked and...

1447
01:48:45,813 --> 01:48:45,980
[Calvin] Oh, so you
haven't seen her back?

1448
01:48:47,940 --> 01:48:48,107
- I haven't...
- No, no, no, no.

1449
01:48:50,484 --> 01:48:50,651
Stephen's right,
you might find this interesting.

1450
01:48:53,571 --> 01:48:53,738
Hildi, go on, take off your dress.
Show Dr. Schultz your back here.

1451
01:48:56,741 --> 01:48:56,907
- Go on.
- [Lara lee] Uh, Calvin.

1452
01:48:59,493 --> 01:48:59,660
I just got her all dressed up
and lookin' nice.

1453
01:49:03,247 --> 01:49:03,414
[Calvin] But, Lara Lee,
Dr. Schultz is from Dusseldorf.

1454
01:49:05,583 --> 01:49:05,750
They don't got niggers there.
He is a man of medicine.

1455
01:49:07,668 --> 01:49:07,877
I'm sure it would fascinate him,
the niggers' endurance for pain.

1456
01:49:08,961 --> 01:49:09,128
These niggers are tough,
Dr. Schultz, no doubt about it.

1457
01:49:11,380 --> 01:49:12,173
Hildi's got somethin'
like four lashes on her back.

1458
01:49:15,217 --> 01:49:16,886
Lara Lee just get one,
she'd lose her goddamn mind.

1459
01:49:19,305 --> 01:49:19,472
- [Stephen] Sure would.
- [Calvin] Look at that, doctor.

1460
01:49:22,141 --> 01:49:23,351
- It's like a paintin'. Look at that.
- Calvin!

1461
01:49:25,144 --> 01:49:31,525
We are eating. Ain't no one wanna
look at her whipped up back.

1462
01:49:33,069 --> 01:49:33,235
- [Exhales]
- Fine. Fine, fine, fine, fine.

1463
01:49:34,904 --> 01:49:36,530
After dinner, then, Stephen.
After dinner.

1464
01:49:39,742 --> 01:49:39,909
During the brandies, gentlemen, hm?

1465
01:49:42,370 --> 01:49:42,536
[Lara lee]
Cora, come get this girl!

1466
01:49:43,871 --> 01:49:50,378
[Approaching footsteps]

1467
01:49:54,173 --> 01:49:54,340
- [Lara lee] She a mess.
- Yes, ma'am. [Gasps] Oh!

1468
01:49:56,300 --> 01:49:57,426
Why are you all undone?
I just got you done up.

1469
01:49:58,511 --> 01:49:58,677
Come on in here.

1470
01:50:04,266 --> 01:50:05,434
Baby, you on Stephen bad side,
and you need to be on his blind side.

1471
01:50:08,813 --> 01:50:10,981
You say you ain't know him.

1472
01:50:12,608 --> 01:50:13,609
Huh?

1473
01:50:13,776 --> 01:50:16,278
I said, you said you ain't know him.

1474
01:50:18,656 --> 01:50:19,990
- I don't.
- Yes, you do.

1475
01:50:20,157 --> 01:50:22,660
Mr. Stephen...

1476
01:50:22,827 --> 01:50:24,995
...I don't.

1477
01:50:25,162 --> 01:50:29,083
Why is you lying to me?

1478
01:50:30,751 --> 01:50:33,838
I ain't.

1479
01:50:34,004 --> 01:50:37,133
Then why is you crying?

1480
01:50:37,299 --> 01:50:40,177
You scarin' me.

1481
01:50:40,344 --> 01:50:43,180
- Why is I'm scaring you?
- Because you scary.

1482
01:50:48,519 --> 01:50:53,023
[Schultz] To speak German
this afternoon with Hildi

1483
01:50:53,190 --> 01:50:56,026
was positively soul-enriching.

1484
01:50:58,028 --> 01:51:03,993
[Calvin] Doctor,
that warms my heart to hear that.

1485
01:51:04,160 --> 01:51:05,536
You stay right here.

1486
01:51:05,703 --> 01:51:07,413
[Schultz] You indicated earlier
you'd be willing to part with Hildi.

1487
01:51:08,038 --> 01:51:09,623
Why,yes.
Yessiree Bob, I did.

1488
01:51:10,666 --> 01:51:13,127
In that case, allow me
to propose another proposition.

1489
01:51:14,253 --> 01:51:16,380
I'm all ears.

1490
01:51:16,547 --> 01:51:19,258
Hurry up, goddamn it!

1491
01:51:19,425 --> 01:51:20,551
- Monsieur Candie...
- [Calvin] Stephen!

1492
01:51:20,718 --> 01:51:24,472
You just interrupted Dr. Schultz here.

1493
01:51:24,638 --> 01:51:26,557
[Stephen] I'm sorry, Dr. Schultz.

1494
01:51:26,724 --> 01:51:30,060
My ears ain't worth a damn these days.

1495
01:51:30,227 --> 01:51:34,064
Excuse him.

1496
01:51:34,231 --> 01:51:36,859
Monsieur Candie, could I get
a word with you in the kitchen?

1497
01:51:37,026 --> 01:51:38,903
You mean get up out of my chair?

1498
01:51:39,069 --> 01:51:41,405
- If'n you could manage it.
- Why?

1499
01:51:41,572 --> 01:51:45,910
- It's about dessert.
- What about dessert?

1500
01:51:46,076 --> 01:51:47,870
I'd rather discuss that in private.

1501
01:51:48,037 --> 01:51:51,123
We're having white cake!

1502
01:51:51,290 --> 01:51:53,167
What sort of melodrama
could be brewing back there?

1503
01:51:53,334 --> 01:51:58,339
You right, Monsieur Candie.
You right. I'll handle it myself.

1504
01:51:58,506 --> 01:51:59,673
[Whispers] Meet me in the library.

1505
01:52:00,591 --> 01:52:04,261
I just can't understand why you
won't come talk to these niggers.

1506
01:52:04,428 --> 01:52:06,180
Shit get fucked up around here,
you blame me.

1507
01:52:06,347 --> 01:52:09,975
Fine! Fine. Friend Stephen,
I will be along momentarily.

1508
01:52:10,142 --> 01:52:11,435
Yessir.

1509
01:52:12,978 --> 01:52:14,772
Well, gentlemen, as you can see,

1510
01:52:20,945 --> 01:52:22,738
talented as they are,
no doubt, in the kitchen,

1511
01:52:24,198 --> 01:52:27,576
from time to time,
adult supervision is required.

1512
01:52:27,743 --> 01:52:33,165
[All chuckle]

1513
01:52:33,332 --> 01:52:36,001
If you'll excuse me a moment.

1514
01:52:36,168 --> 01:52:37,670
[Calvin] You may clear
the dinner service.

1515
01:52:42,466 --> 01:52:44,260
[Cora] You heard him. Go on!
Get! Hurry up, girl.

1516
01:52:49,515 --> 01:52:54,603
So, Dr. Schultz, why don't you
regale us with a tale of the circus.

1517
01:52:54,770 --> 01:52:58,315
[Chuckles] The circus?

1518
01:52:58,482 --> 01:53:01,235
[Fire crackling]

1519
01:53:01,402 --> 01:53:04,572
What is the matter?

1520
01:53:04,738 --> 01:53:08,409
Them motherfuckers
ain't here to buy no Mandingos.

1521
01:53:08,576 --> 01:53:10,744
- They wants that girl.
- [Chuckling]

1522
01:53:10,911 --> 01:53:13,539
Stephen, what the hell
are you talKing about? Hm?

1523
01:53:13,706 --> 01:53:17,334
They playing your ass for a fool
is what I'm talKing about.

1524
01:53:19,044 --> 01:53:20,629
They ain't here for
no musclebound jimmie.

1525
01:53:20,796 --> 01:53:23,173
They here for that girl.

1526
01:53:23,340 --> 01:53:25,801
Wh... what girl? Hildi?

1527
01:53:25,968 --> 01:53:28,220
Yeah, Hildi. Her and Django,
them niggers know each other.

1528
01:53:28,387 --> 01:53:31,599
He just bought Eskimo Joe.

1529
01:53:31,765 --> 01:53:34,768
- Did he give you any money?
- No! Not yet. But...

1530
01:53:40,190 --> 01:53:42,192
Then he ain't bought diddly.
Not yet, nohow.

1531
01:53:43,319 --> 01:53:45,112
But he's just about to buy

1532
01:53:45,279 --> 01:53:47,781
who he come here to buy
when I interrupted him.

1533
01:53:47,948 --> 01:53:52,244
"Thank you, Stephen."
You're welcome, Calvin.

1534
01:53:52,411 --> 01:53:54,246
Where you gettin' all this?

1535
01:53:54,413 --> 01:53:57,207
Why would they go through
all that trouble for a nigger

1536
01:53:57,374 --> 01:54:00,461
with a chewed up back,
ain't worth $300?

1537
01:54:03,047 --> 01:54:05,007
They doin' it 'cause that nigger
Django's in love with Hildi.

1538
01:54:05,591 --> 01:54:09,887
She probably his wife.

1539
01:54:10,054 --> 01:54:13,557
Now, why that German gives a fuck
who that uppity son of a bitch

1540
01:54:13,724 --> 01:54:19,188
is in love with,
I'm sure I don't know.

1541
01:54:21,899 --> 01:54:23,567
If she's who they want...

1542
01:54:26,904 --> 01:54:28,530
...why this whole snake oil pitch
about Mandingos, then?

1543
01:54:32,409 --> 01:54:36,121
You wouldn't pay no
never mind to no $300.

1544
01:54:36,288 --> 01:54:37,706
But that 12,000? That made you
real friendly, now, didn't it?

1545
01:54:39,416 --> 01:54:41,418
Yes, it did.

1546
01:54:42,252 --> 01:54:48,258
His wife, huh?

1547
01:54:50,469 --> 01:54:51,637
If it had been a snake,
it would have bit me.

1548
01:54:52,262 --> 01:54:57,059
[Chuckles]

1549
01:54:58,310 --> 01:54:59,770
Those lying...

1550
01:54:59,937 --> 01:55:02,731
...goddamn time-wastin'
sons of bitches.

1551
01:55:02,898 --> 01:55:04,358
Sons of bitches!

1552
01:55:04,525 --> 01:55:06,694
...out of New Orleans, so I have quite
a bit of practice with theater types.

1553
01:55:06,860 --> 01:55:09,947
Oh, there you are.

1554
01:55:10,114 --> 01:55:13,158
I was beginning to think that you
and that old crow run off together.

1555
01:55:13,325 --> 01:55:14,410
[All chuckling]

1556
01:55:14,576 --> 01:55:18,455
That'd be a hell of a note, wouldn't it?

1557
01:55:18,622 --> 01:55:20,874
Lara Lee, I was just
looKing out the big window.

1558
01:55:34,138 --> 01:55:37,850
Billy crash is out there
dealing with some shady slaver

1559
01:55:39,893 --> 01:55:42,813
trying to sell a passel of ponies.

1560
01:55:42,980 --> 01:55:46,984
Would you be a dear, go out there
and give them gals an eyeball? Hm?

1561
01:55:47,151 --> 01:55:50,070
- Of course, brother.
- Thank you, darling.

1562
01:55:50,237 --> 01:55:52,364
- Yeah. Business never sleeps.
- Hm-mm.

1563
01:56:08,839 --> 01:56:10,883
Apropos, before your exit,

1564
01:56:13,260 --> 01:56:14,303
we were discussing the possibility
of my purchasing Broomhilda.

1565
01:56:15,846 --> 01:56:17,347
Ah, yes. Yes, we were, doctor.

1566
01:56:18,682 --> 01:56:23,687
And we will again. In a moment.

1567
01:56:23,854 --> 01:56:26,273
Who's your little friend?

1568
01:56:27,357 --> 01:56:31,111
[Clearing throat]

1569
01:56:31,987 --> 01:56:34,031
This is Ben.

1570
01:56:34,198 --> 01:56:36,784
He's a old Joe that
lived around here for a long time.

1571
01:56:39,620 --> 01:56:41,288
And I do mean a long damn time.

1572
01:56:43,874 --> 01:56:47,669
Old Ben here took care of my daddy...

1573
01:56:47,836 --> 01:56:53,717
...and my daddy's daddy.

1574
01:56:55,344 --> 01:57:00,641
Till he up and keeled over one day...

1575
01:57:01,892 --> 01:57:05,687
...old Ben took care of me.

1576
01:57:07,731 --> 01:57:10,067
Growing up the son of a huge
plantation owner in Miss.issippi

1577
01:57:10,234 --> 01:57:13,403
puts a white man in contact
with a whole lotta black faces.

1578
01:57:17,115 --> 01:57:19,576
I spent my whole life here,
right here in Candyland...

1579
01:57:22,579 --> 01:57:27,751
...surrounded by black faces.

1580
01:57:27,918 --> 01:57:32,840
Now, seeing them every day,
day in, day out,

1581
01:57:33,006 --> 01:57:38,136
I only had one question:

1582
01:57:38,303 --> 01:57:41,723
- Why don't they kill us?
- [Laughs]

1583
01:57:44,268 --> 01:57:45,769
Now, right out there on that porch,
three times a week for 50 years,

1584
01:57:47,646 --> 01:57:48,939
old Ben here would
shave my daddy with a straight razor.

1585
01:57:50,315 --> 01:57:55,112
Now, if I was old Ben, I woulda
cut my daddy's goddamn throat

1586
01:57:55,279 --> 01:58:00,367
and it wouldn't have taken me
no 50 years to do it, neither.

1587
01:58:02,202 --> 01:58:05,914
But he never did.

1588
01:58:06,081 --> 01:58:08,208
Why not?

1589
01:58:08,375 --> 01:58:13,881
You see, the science of phrenology

1590
01:58:14,965 --> 01:58:16,633
is crucial to understanding
the separation of our two species.

1591
01:58:29,396 --> 01:58:31,356
In the skull of the African here,

1592
01:58:32,733 --> 01:58:34,902
the area associated
with subMiss.iveness

1593
01:58:41,199 --> 01:58:44,786
is larger than any human or any other
subhuman species on planet earth.

1594
01:58:48,498 --> 01:58:48,665
[Sawing]

1595
01:58:49,916 --> 01:58:50,083
If you examine...

1596
01:58:55,088 --> 01:58:55,255
...this piece of skull here...

1597
01:58:57,758 --> 01:58:57,924
...you will notice
three distinct dimples.

1598
01:59:01,261 --> 01:59:01,928
Here, here and here.

1599
01:59:03,764 --> 01:59:04,389
Now...

1600
01:59:06,516 --> 01:59:06,683
...if I was holding the skull
of an Isaac Newton or Galileo,

1601
01:59:08,977 --> 01:59:09,144
these three dimples would be
found in the area of the skull

1602
01:59:13,315 --> 01:59:14,441
most associated with... creativity.

1603
01:59:15,776 --> 01:59:16,777
But this is the skull of old Ben.

1604
01:59:18,528 --> 01:59:19,446
And in the skull of old Ben,

1605
01:59:21,615 --> 01:59:24,076
unburdened by genius,

1606
01:59:26,161 --> 01:59:28,288
these three dimples exist in the area
of the skull most associated with...

1607
01:59:30,624 --> 01:59:31,625
...servility.

1608
01:59:36,963 --> 01:59:38,215
Now, bright boy...

1609
01:59:39,674 --> 01:59:40,801
...I will admit you are pretty clever.

1610
01:59:44,388 --> 01:59:44,554
But if I took this hammer here...

1611
01:59:47,516 --> 01:59:47,682
...and I bashed in your skull with it...

1612
01:59:50,936 --> 01:59:52,020
...you would have the same
three dimples in the same place...

1613
01:59:55,148 --> 01:59:55,315
...as old Ben.

1614
01:59:57,651 --> 01:59:57,818
Hey! Now lay your palms
flat on that tabletop!

1615
02:00:00,612 --> 02:00:00,779
If you lift those palms
off that turtle shell tabletop,

1616
02:00:03,156 --> 02:00:07,869
Mr. Pooch is gonna let loose
with both barrels of that sawed-off.

1617
02:00:10,288 --> 02:00:14,835
There have been a lot of lies said
around this dinner table here tonight,

1618
02:00:16,211 --> 02:00:20,674
but that you can believe!

1619
02:00:22,092 --> 02:00:26,096
Mr. Moguy, would you be
so kind as to collect the pistol

1620
02:00:27,597 --> 02:00:27,764
hanging off these boys' hips here?

1621
02:00:30,517 --> 02:00:30,684
- Thank you ever so much.
- Doctor.

1622
02:00:33,145 --> 02:00:33,311
Where were we?

1623
02:00:34,688 --> 02:00:38,692
Jackass.

1624
02:00:40,026 --> 02:00:42,446
Ah, yes.

1625
02:00:43,947 --> 02:00:46,700
I do believe you were
just getting ready to make me

1626
02:00:48,243 --> 02:00:49,703
a proposition to buy Broomhilda.

1627
02:00:51,955 --> 02:00:52,122
Am I right?

1628
02:00:53,373 --> 02:00:53,540
Right.

1629
02:00:55,083 --> 02:00:59,379
Bring out Hildi!

1630
02:01:01,965 --> 02:01:02,132
Get over there yonder.

1631
02:01:04,885 --> 02:01:05,051
- [Screams]
- Sit your ass in that goddamn...

1632
02:01:09,389 --> 02:01:09,556
[Stephen] Lay your hand
flat on that tabletop.

1633
02:01:12,601 --> 02:01:12,767
[Calvin] Now shut your mouth!

1634
02:01:16,730 --> 02:01:17,522
Dr. Schultz, in Greenville,

1635
02:01:19,274 --> 02:01:19,441
you yourself said that
for the right nigger

1636
02:01:21,401 --> 02:01:21,568
you'd be willin' to pay what some
may consider is a ridiculous amount.

1637
02:01:25,530 --> 02:01:25,697
To which me myself said,
"what is your definition of ridiculous?"

1638
02:01:28,116 --> 02:01:28,283
To which you said, "$12,000."

1639
02:01:34,247 --> 02:01:34,414
- [Yells]
- Now, considering y'all

1640
02:01:38,168 --> 02:01:38,335
have ridden a whole lot of Miles,

1641
02:01:43,965 --> 02:01:44,132
went through a whole lot of trouble,
and done spread a whole lot of bull

1642
02:01:47,928 --> 02:01:50,180
to purchase this
lovely lady right here,

1643
02:01:51,723 --> 02:01:52,557
it would appear that Broomhilda is,
in fact... the right nigger.

1644
02:01:55,560 --> 02:01:55,727
And if y'all want to leave
Candyland with Broomhilda,

1645
02:01:59,272 --> 02:01:59,439
the price is $12,000.

1646
02:02:04,569 --> 02:02:05,654
And I take it you prefer the "take it
or leave it" style of negotiation?

1647
02:02:07,948 --> 02:02:08,615
Yes, I do, doctor.

1648
02:02:11,326 --> 02:02:11,493
You see,
under the laws of chickasaw county,

1649
02:02:14,955 --> 02:02:18,875
Broomhilda here is my property.

1650
02:02:22,003 --> 02:02:22,170
And I can choose to do with
my property whatever I so desire!

1651
02:02:24,297 --> 02:02:24,464
And if y'all think my price...

1652
02:02:28,969 --> 02:02:29,135
...for this nigger here
is too steep...

1653
02:02:33,306 --> 02:02:33,473
- [Grunts]
- ...What I'm gonna desire to do is...

1654
02:02:34,808 --> 02:02:34,975
...take this goddamn hammer here
and beat her ass to death with it!

1655
02:02:38,853 --> 02:02:40,063
- Right in front of both y'all!
- Easy, big fella.

1656
02:02:41,398 --> 02:02:49,398
Then we can examine the three dimples
inside Broomhilda's skull!

1657
02:02:56,371 --> 02:03:00,417
Now, what's it gonna be, doc?
Huh?

1658
02:03:02,294 --> 02:03:02,460
- [Hildi whimpering]
- What's it gonna be?

1659
02:03:05,005 --> 02:03:05,171
May I lift the hands off the tabletop
in order to remove my billfold?

1660
02:03:08,508 --> 02:03:14,347
Yes, you may.

1661
02:03:16,641 --> 02:03:16,808
That 12.

1662
02:03:20,478 --> 02:03:20,645
- Sold!
- [Screaming]

1663
02:03:22,397 --> 02:03:25,525
To the man with the exceptional beard

1664
02:03:27,694 --> 02:03:28,570
and his unexceptional nigger.

1665
02:03:30,322 --> 02:03:31,531
- Mr. Moguy.
- Yes, Calvin?

1666
02:03:33,408 --> 02:03:34,367
Will you make these gentlemen
a receipt for $12,000, please?

1667
02:03:36,828 --> 02:03:37,704
$12,000.

1668
02:03:39,331 --> 02:03:47,331
It was a pleasure doing
business with y'all.

1669
02:04:37,305 --> 02:04:45,305
Now, gentlemen...

1670
02:04:54,155 --> 02:05:02,155
...if you care to
join me in the parlor...

1671
02:05:06,501 --> 02:05:09,003
...we will be serving white cake.

1672
02:05:11,881 --> 02:05:13,341
[Beethoven's "fur elise"
played on harp]

1673
02:05:17,011 --> 02:05:21,266
- [Screaming]
- [Dogs snarling]

1674
02:05:22,350 --> 02:05:22,517
[Screaming]

